MedicalClinic.description: A facility, often associated with a hospital or medical school, that is devoted to the specific diagnosis and/or healthcare. Previously limited to outpatients but with evolution it may be open to inpatients as well.

LikeAction.name: LikeAction
LikeAction.description: The act of expressing a positive sentiment about the object. An agent likes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

VitalSign.name: VitalSign
VitalSign.description: Vital signs are measures of various physiological functions in order to assess the most basic body functions.

UKNonprofitType.name: UKNonprofitType
UKNonprofitType.description: UKNonprofitType: Non-profit organization type originating from the United Kingdom.

FindAction.name: FindAction
FindAction.description:
The act of finding an object.

Related actions:

* [[SearchAction]]: FindAction is generally lead by a SearchAction, but not necessarily.

DepositAccount.name: DepositAccount
DepositAccount.description: A type of Bank Account with a main purpose of depositing funds to gain interest or other benefits.

AskPublicNewsArticle.name: AskPublicNewsArticle
AskPublicNewsArticle.description: A [[NewsArticle]] expressing an open call by a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] asking the public for input, insights, clarifications, anecdotes, documentation, etc., on an issue, for reporting purposes.

QuoteAction.name: QuoteAction
QuoteAction.description: An agent quotes/estimates/appraises an object/product/service with a price at a location/store.

AMRadioChannel.name: AMRadioChannel
AMRadioChannel.description: A radio channel that uses AM.

AccountingService.name: AccountingService
AccountingService.description: Accountancy business.\n\nAs a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\(s).

SearchResultsPage.name: SearchResultsPage
SearchResultsPage.description: Web page type: Search results page.

AdultOrientedEnumeration.name: AdultOrientedEnumeration
AdultOrientedEnumeration.description: Enumeration of considerations that make a product relevant or potentially restricted for adults only.

Periodical.name: Periodical
Periodical.description: A publication in any medium issued in successive parts bearing numerical or chronological designations and intended to continue indefinitely, such as a magazine, scholarly journal, or newspaper.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

IndividualPhysician.name: IndividualPhysician
IndividualPhysician.description: An individual medical practitioner. For their official address use [[address]], for affiliations to hospitals use [[hospitalAffiliation]]. The [[practicesAt]] property can be used to indicate [[MedicalOrganization]] hospitals, clinics, pharmacies etc. where this physician practices.

WearAction.name: WearAction
WearAction.description: The act of dressing oneself in clothing.

MedicalTest.name: MedicalTest
MedicalTest.description: Any medical test, typically performed for diagnostic purposes.

MedicalSymptom.name: MedicalSymptom
MedicalSymptom.description: Any complaint sensed and expressed by the patient (therefore defined as subjective) like stomachache, lower-back pain, or fatigue.

FAQPage.name: FAQPage
FAQPage.description: A [[FAQPage]] is a [[WebPage]] presenting one or more "[Frequently asked questions](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FAQ)" (see also [[QAPage]]).

TrackAction.name: TrackAction
TrackAction.description:
An agent tracks an object for updates.

Related actions:

* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, TrackAction refers to the interest on the location of innanimates objects.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, TrackAction refers to the interest on the location of innanimate objects.

AudioObjectSnapshot.name: AudioObjectSnapshot
AudioObjectSnapshot.description: A specific and exact (byte-for-byte) version of an [[AudioObject]]. Two byte-for-byte identical files, for the purposes of this type, considered identical. If they have different embedded metadata the files will differ. Different external facts about the files, e.g. creator or dateCreated that aren't represented in their actual content, do not affect this notion of identity.

DayOfWeek.name: DayOfWeek
DayOfWeek.description: The day of the week, e.g. used to specify to which day the opening hours of an OpeningHoursSpecification refer. Originally, URLs from [GoodRelations](http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1) were used (for [[Monday]], [[Tuesday]], [[Wednesday]], [[Thursday]], [[Friday]], [[Saturday]], [[Sunday]] plus a special entry for [[PublicHolidays]]); these have now been integrated directly into schema.org.

OfferCatalog.name: OfferCatalog
OfferCatalog.description: An OfferCatalog is an ItemList that contains related Offers and/or further OfferCatalogs that are offeredBy the same provider.

Distance.name: Distance
Distance.description: Properties that take Distances as values are of the form '<Number> <Length unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 ft'.

BorrowAction.name: BorrowAction
BorrowAction.description:
The act of obtaining an object under an agreement to return it at a later date. Reciprocal of LendAction.

Related actions:

* [[LendAction]]: Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

Article.name: Article
Article.description: An article, such as a news article or piece of investigative report. Newspapers and magazines have articles of many different types and this is intended to cover them all.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

ActionAccessSpecification.name: ActionAccessSpecification
ActionAccessSpecification.description: A set of requirements that must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action.

TouristAttraction.name: TouristAttraction
TouristAttraction.description: A tourist attraction. In principle any Thing can be a [[TouristAttraction]], from a [[Mountain]] and [[LandmarksOrHistoricalBuildings]] to a [[LocalBusiness]]. This Type can be used on its own to describe a general [[TouristAttraction]], or be used as an [[additionalType]] to add tourist attraction properties to any other type. (See examples below)

EntryPoint.name: EntryPoint
EntryPoint.description: An entry point, within some Web-based protocol.

Thesis.name: Thesis
Thesis.description: A thesis or dissertation document submitted in support of candidature for an academic degree or professional qualification.

StatusEnumeration.name: StatusEnumeration
StatusEnumeration.description: Lists or enumerations dealing with status types.

Nerve.name: Nerve
Nerve.description: A common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons.

MeetingRoom.name: MeetingRoom
MeetingRoom.description: A meeting room, conference room, or conference hall is a room provided for singular events such as business conferences and meetings (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_hall). See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

DataFeedItem.name: DataFeedItem
DataFeedItem.description: A single item within a larger data feed.

Muscle.name: Muscle
Muscle.description: A muscle is an anatomical structure consisting of a contractile form of tissue that animals use to effect movement.

DrugPregnancyCategory.name: DrugPregnancyCategory
DrugPregnancyCategory.description: Categories that represent an assessment of the risk of fetal injury due to a drug or pharmaceutical used as directed by the mother during pregnancy.

OperatingSystem.name: OperatingSystem
OperatingSystem.description: System software that manages computer hardware and software resources, and provides common services for computer programs.

JoinAction.name: JoinAction
JoinAction.description:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates.

legislationPassedBy.name: legislationPassedBy
legislationPassedBy.description: The person or organization that originally passed or made the law: typically parliament (for primary legislation) or government (for secondary legislation). This indicates the "legal author" of the law, as opposed to its physical author.

funding.name: funding
funding.description: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

valuePattern.name: valuePattern
valuePattern.description: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

provider.name: provider
provider.description: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

honorificPrefix.name: honorificPrefix
honorificPrefix.description: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

modifiedTime.name: modifiedTime
modifiedTime.description: The date and time the reservation was modified.

numberOfCredits.name: numberOfCredits
numberOfCredits.description: The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

noBylinesPolicy.name: noBylinesPolicy
noBylinesPolicy.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement explaining when authors of articles are not named in bylines.

genre.name: genre
genre.description: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

sameAs.name: sameAs
sameAs.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

wordCount.name: wordCount
wordCount.description: The number of words in the text of the CreativeWork such as an Article, Book, etc.

recommendedIntake.name: recommendedIntake
recommendedIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

isGift.name: isGift
isGift.description: Indicates whether the offer was accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

interactingDrug.name: interactingDrug
interactingDrug.description: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

experienceInPlaceOfEducation.name: experienceInPlaceOfEducation
experienceInPlaceOfEducation.description: Indicates whether a [[JobPosting]] will accept experience (as indicated by [[OccupationalExperienceRequirements]]) in place of its formal educational qualifications (as indicated by [[educationRequirements]]). If true, indicates that satisfying one of these requirements is sufficient.

isProprietary.name: isProprietary
isProprietary.description: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

accessModeSufficient.name: accessModeSufficient
accessModeSufficient.description: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessModeSufficient-vocabulary).

breadcrumb.name: breadcrumb
breadcrumb.description: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

recordedAs.name: recordedAs
recordedAs.description: An audio recording of the work.

vehicleConfiguration.name: vehicleConfiguration
vehicleConfiguration.description: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

orderItemNumber.name: orderItemNumber
orderItemNumber.description: The identifier of the order item.

legislationIdentifier.name: legislationIdentifier
legislationIdentifier.description: An identifier for the legislation. This can be either a string-based identifier, like the CELEX at EU level or the NOR in France, or a web-based, URL/URI identifier, like an ELI (European Legislation Identifier) or an URN-Lex.

weightTotal.name: weightTotal
weightTotal.description:
The permitted total weight of the loaded vehicle, including passengers and cargo and the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

numberOfFullBathrooms.name: numberOfFullBathrooms
numberOfFullBathrooms.description: Number of full bathrooms - The total number of full and  bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsFull field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsFull+Field).

readBy.name: readBy
readBy.description: A person who reads (performs) the audiobook.

readonlyValue.name: readonlyValue
readonlyValue.description: Whether or not a property is mutable. Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

containsSeason.name: containsSeason
containsSeason.description: A season that is part of the media series.

legislationCommences.name: legislationCommences
legislationCommences.description: Another legislation that this one sets into force.

pickupTime.name: pickupTime
pickupTime.description: When a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

hoursAvailable.name: hoursAvailable
hoursAvailable.description: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

targetPlatform.name: targetPlatform
targetPlatform.description: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

connectedTo.name: connectedTo
connectedTo.description: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

cvdNumBedsOcc.name: cvdNumBedsOcc
cvdNumBedsOcc.description: numbedsocc - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient beds that are occupied.

nonEqual.name: nonEqual
nonEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

qualifiedExpense.name: qualifiedExpense
qualifiedExpense.description: Optional. The types of expenses that are covered by the incentive. For example some incentives are only for the goods (tangible items) but the services (labor) are excluded.

paymentUrl.name: paymentUrl
paymentUrl.description: The URL for sending a payment.

acquireLicensePage.name: acquireLicensePage
acquireLicensePage.description: Indicates a page documenting how licenses can be purchased or otherwise acquired, for the current item.

hasRepresentation.name: hasRepresentation
hasRepresentation.description: A common representation such as a protein sequence or chemical structure for this entity. For images use schema.org/image.

suggestedMinAge.name: suggestedMinAge
suggestedMinAge.description: Minimum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

polygon.name: polygon
polygon.description: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

duration.name: duration
duration.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

maximumEnrollment.name: maximumEnrollment
maximumEnrollment.description: The maximum number of students who may be enrolled in the program.

numberOfForwardGears.name: numberOfForwardGears
numberOfForwardGears.description: The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

taxonRank.name: taxonRank
taxonRank.description: The taxonomic rank of this taxon given preferably as a URI from a controlled vocabulary  typically the ranks from TDWG TaxonRank ontology or equivalent Wikidata URIs.

actionPlatform.name: actionPlatform
actionPlatform.description: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

numTracks.name: numTracks
numTracks.description: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

legislationLegalValue.name: legislationLegalValue
legislationLegalValue.description: The legal value of this legislation file. The same legislation can be written in multiple files with different legal values. Typically a digitally signed PDF have a "stronger" legal value than the HTML file of the same act.

sensoryRequirement.name: sensoryRequirement
sensoryRequirement.description: A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

hasDefinedTerm.name: hasDefinedTerm
hasDefinedTerm.description: A Defined Term contained in this term set.

geoCovers.name: geoCovers
geoCovers.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

mathExpression.name: mathExpression
mathExpression.description: A mathematical expression (e.g. 'x^2-3x=0') that may be solved for a specific variable, simplified, or transformed. This can take many formats, e.g. LaTeX, Ascii-Math, or math as you would write with a keyboard.

lender.name: lender
lender.description: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

temporalCoverage.name: temporalCoverage
temporalCoverage.description: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in [ISO 8601 time interval format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Time_intervals). In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content, e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode, may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945". Open-ended date ranges can be written with ".." in place of the end date. For example, "2015-11/.." indicates a range beginning in November 2015 and with no specified final date. This is tentative and might be updated in future when ISO 8601 is officially updated.

shippingDetails.name: shippingDetails
shippingDetails.description: Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an [[Offer]].

specialOpeningHoursSpecification.name: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
specialOpeningHoursSpecification.description: The special opening hours of a certain place.\n\nUse this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by [[openingHoursSpecification]] or [[openingHours]].

publicAccess.name: publicAccess
publicAccess.description: A flag to signal that the [[Place]] is open to public visitors. If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value.

structuralClass.name: structuralClass
structuralClass.description: The name given to how bone physically connects to each other.

smokingAllowed.name: smokingAllowed
smokingAllowed.description: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

currenciesAccepted.name: currenciesAccepted
currenciesAccepted.description: The currency accepted.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

publisher.name: publisher
publisher.description: The publisher of the article in question.

targetUrl.name: targetUrl
targetUrl.description: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

endOffset.name: endOffset
endOffset.description: The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

eligibleDuration.name: eligibleDuration
eligibleDuration.description: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

costCurrency.name: costCurrency
costCurrency.description: The currency (in 3-letter) of the drug cost. See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217.

hasMeasurement.name: hasMeasurement
hasMeasurement.description: A measurement of an item, For example, the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, the gauge of a screw, or the carbon footprint measured for certification by an authority. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

vehicleTransmission.name: vehicleTransmission
vehicleTransmission.description: The type of component used for transmitting the power from a rotating power source to the wheels or other relevant component(s) ("gearbox" for cars).

reportNumber.name: reportNumber
reportNumber.description: The number or other unique designator assigned to a Report by the publishing organization.

exerciseCourse.name: exerciseCourse
exerciseCourse.description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

knownVehicleDamages.name: knownVehicleDamages
knownVehicleDamages.description: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

warranty.name: warranty
warranty.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

distribution.name: distribution
distribution.description: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format. This property can be repeated if different variations are available. There is no expectation that different downloadable distributions must contain exactly equivalent information (see also [DCAT](https://www.w3.org/TR/vocab-dcat-3/#Class:Distribution) on this point). Different distributions might include or exclude different subsets of the entire dataset, for example.

actionAccessibilityRequirement.name: actionAccessibilityRequirement
actionAccessibilityRequirement.description: A set of requirements that must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specified, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

numberOfAccommodationUnits.name: numberOfAccommodationUnits
numberOfAccommodationUnits.description: Indicates the total (available plus unavailable) number of accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits]].

weight.name: weight
weight.description: The weight of the product or person.

associatedArticle.name: associatedArticle
associatedArticle.description: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

commentTime.name: commentTime
commentTime.description: The time at which the UserComment was made.

steeringPosition.name: steeringPosition
steeringPosition.description: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

legislationConsolidates.name: legislationConsolidates
legislationConsolidates.description: Indicates another legislation taken into account in this consolidated legislation (which is usually the product of an editorial process that revises the legislation). This property should be used multiple times to refer to both the original version or the previous consolidated version, and to the legislations making the change.

hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory.name: hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory
hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (which could be either a rating out of range of values or a yes/no certification) for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

reservationFor.name: reservationFor
reservationFor.description: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant, etc. being reserved.

cssSelector.name: cssSelector
cssSelector.description: A CSS selector, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

proficiencyLevel.name: proficiencyLevel
proficiencyLevel.description: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

question.name: question
question.description: A sub property of object. A question.

thumbnail.name: thumbnail
thumbnail.description: Thumbnail image for an image or video.

strengthUnit.name: strengthUnit
strengthUnit.description: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

propertyID.name: propertyID
propertyID.description: A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be (1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific ID of the property), or (3) a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry). Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

servicePostalAddress.name: servicePostalAddress
servicePostalAddress.description: The address for accessing the service by mail.

billingDuration.name: billingDuration
billingDuration.description: Specifies for how long this price (or price component) will be billed. Can be used, for example, to model the contractual duration of a subscription or payment plan. Type can be either a Duration or a Number (in which case the unit of measurement, for example month, is specified by the unitCode property).

additionalNumberOfGuests.name: additionalNumberOfGuests
additionalNumberOfGuests.description: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

thumbnailUrl.name: thumbnailUrl
thumbnailUrl.description: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

mediaAuthenticityCategory.name: mediaAuthenticityCategory
mediaAuthenticityCategory.description: Indicates a MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration classification of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared).

geoOverlaps.name: geoOverlaps
geoOverlaps.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

inAlbum.name: inAlbum
inAlbum.description: The album to which this recording belongs.

commentCount.name: commentCount
commentCount.description: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

availableThrough.name: availableThrough
availableThrough.description: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

busNumber.name: busNumber
busNumber.description: The unique identifier for the bus.

guidelineSubject.name: guidelineSubject
guidelineSubject.description: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

refundType.name: refundType
refundType.description: A refund type, from an enumerated list.

addressCountry.name: addressCountry
addressCountry.description: The country. Recommended to be in 2-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1) format, for example "US". For backward compatibility, a 3-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-3](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1_alpha-3) country code such as "SGP" or a full country name such as "Singapore" can also be used.

customer.name: customer
customer.description: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

hasMenuItem.name: hasMenuItem
hasMenuItem.description: A food or drink item contained in a menu or menu section.

displayLocation.name: displayLocation
displayLocation.description: The location at which an item can be viewed or experienced in-person.

roofLoad.name: roofLoad
roofLoad.description:
The permitted total weight of cargo and installations (e.g. a roof rack) on top of the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]]
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

latitude.name: latitude
latitude.description: The latitude of a location. For example ```37.42242``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

coverageStartTime.name: coverageStartTime
coverageStartTime.description: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

medicalSpecialty.name: medicalSpecialty
medicalSpecialty.description: A medical specialty of the provider.

emissionsCO2.name: emissionsCO2
emissionsCO2.description: The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".

webCheckinTime.name: webCheckinTime
webCheckinTime.description: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

experienceRequirements.name: experienceRequirements
experienceRequirements.description: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

printPage.name: printPage
printPage.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

fatContent.name: fatContent
fatContent.description: The number of grams of fat.

knowsAbout.name: knowsAbout
knowsAbout.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or [[JobPosting]] descriptions.

syllabusSections.name: syllabusSections
syllabusSections.description: Indicates (typically several) Syllabus entities that lay out what each section of the overall course will cover.

gtin.name: gtin
gtin.description: A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes. A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also [GS1's GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) and [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number) for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged. The [[gtin]] property generalizes the earlier [[gtin8]], [[gtin12]], [[gtin13]], and [[gtin14]] properties. The GS1 [digital link specifications](https://www.gs1.org/standards/Digital-Link/) expresses GTINs as URLs (URIs, IRIs, etc.). Digital Links should be populated into the [[hasGS1DigitalLink]] attribute. Note also that this is a definition for how to include GTINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of GTINs in general - see the GS1 documentation for authoritative details.

orderDelivery.name: orderDelivery
orderDelivery.description: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

archivedAt.name: archivedAt
archivedAt.description: Indicates a page or other link involved in archival of a [[CreativeWork]]. In the case of [[MediaReview]], the items in a [[MediaReviewItem]] may often become inaccessible, but be archived by archival, journalistic, activist, or law enforcement organizations. In such cases, the referenced page may not directly publish the content.

cholesterolContent.name: cholesterolContent
cholesterolContent.description: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

workPresented.name: workPresented
workPresented.description: The movie presented during this event.

broker.name: broker
broker.description: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller. In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange. If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

epidemiology.name: epidemiology
epidemiology.description: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

numberOfRooms.name: numberOfRooms
numberOfRooms.description: The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business. Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

checkoutPageURLTemplate.name: checkoutPageURLTemplate
checkoutPageURLTemplate.description: A URL template (RFC 6570) for a checkout page for an offer. This approach allows merchants to specify a URL for online checkout of the offered product, by interpolating parameters such as the logged in user ID, product ID, quantity, discount code etc. Parameter naming and standardization are not specified here.

fileSize.name: fileSize
fileSize.description: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

expectedPrognosis.name: expectedPrognosis
expectedPrognosis.description: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

countriesSupported.name: countriesSupported
countriesSupported.description: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

signOrSymptom.name: signOrSymptom
signOrSymptom.description: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

openingHoursSpecification.name: openingHoursSpecification
openingHoursSpecification.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

vehicleInteriorType.name: vehicleInteriorType
vehicleInteriorType.description: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

partOfInvoice.name: partOfInvoice
partOfInvoice.description: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

data.name: data
data.description: Data associated with the event, like for instance a log message.

scheduledPaymentDate.name: scheduledPaymentDate
scheduledPaymentDate.description: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

geoRadius.name: geoRadius
geoRadius.description: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

occupationLocation.name: occupationLocation
occupationLocation.description: The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

validIn.name: validIn
validIn.description: The geographic area where the item is valid. Applies for example to a [[Permit]], a [[Certification]], or an [[EducationalOccupationalCredential]].

exerciseRelatedDiet.name: exerciseRelatedDiet
exerciseRelatedDiet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

digitalSourceType.name: digitalSourceType
digitalSourceType.description: Indicates an IPTCDigitalSourceEnumeration code indicating the nature of the digital source(s) for some [[CreativeWork]].

normalRange.name: normalRange
normalRange.description: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

broadcastOfEvent.name: broadcastOfEvent
broadcastOfEvent.description: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

stage.name: stage
stage.description: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

boardingPolicy.name: boardingPolicy
boardingPolicy.description: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

issn.name: issn
issn.description: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

instructor.name: instructor
instructor.description: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the [[CourseInstance]].

educationalCredentialAwarded.name: educationalCredentialAwarded
educationalCredentialAwarded.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

transcript.name: transcript
transcript.description: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

byMonth.name: byMonth
byMonth.description: Defines the month(s) of the year on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-12. January is 1.

freeShippingThreshold.name: freeShippingThreshold
freeShippingThreshold.description: A monetary value above (or at) which the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with [[shippingSettingsLink]] matching this [[ShippingRateSettings]].

discusses.name: discusses
discusses.description: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

requiredGender.name: requiredGender
requiredGender.description: Audiences defined by a person's gender.

termsPerYear.name: termsPerYear
termsPerYear.description: The number of times terms of study are offered per year. Semesters and quarters are common units for term. For example, if the student can only take 2 semesters for the program in one year, then termsPerYear should be 2.

source.name: source
source.description: The source or cause of the event.

assesses.name: assesses
assesses.description: The item being described is intended to assess the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

isStoreOn.name: isStoreOn
isStoreOn.description: The eCommerce marketplace this online store is on.

relevantSpecialty.name: relevantSpecialty
relevantSpecialty.description: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

gtin12.name: gtin12
gtin12.description: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

upvoteCount.name: upvoteCount
upvoteCount.description: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

hasCourseInstance.name: hasCourseInstance
hasCourseInstance.description: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

usNPI.name: usNPI
usNPI.description: A National Provider Identifier (NPI) is a unique 10-digit identification number issued to health care providers in the United States by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services.

price.name: price
price.description:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.

result.name: result
result.description: The result produced in the action. E.g. John wrote *a book*.

geoContains.name: geoContains
geoContains.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

featureList.name: featureList
featureList.description: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

hasMenuSection.name: hasMenuSection
hasMenuSection.description: A subgrouping of the menu (by dishes, course, serving time period, etc.).

license.name: license
license.description: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

salaryUponCompletion.name: salaryUponCompletion
salaryUponCompletion.description: The expected salary upon completing the training.

query.name: query
query.description: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

gender.name: gender
gender.description: Gender of something, typically a [[Person]], but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While https://schema.org/Male and https://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who are not a binary gender. The [[gender]] property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender [[SportsTeam]] can be indicated with a text value of "Mixed".

processorRequirements.name: processorRequirements
processorRequirements.description: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

totalHistoricalEnrollment.name: totalHistoricalEnrollment
totalHistoricalEnrollment.description: The total number of students that have enrolled in the history of the course.

foundingDate.name: foundingDate
foundingDate.description: The date that this organization was founded.

missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy.name: missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy
missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement on coverage priorities, including any public agenda or stance on issues.

eduQuestionType.name: eduQuestionType
eduQuestionType.description: For questions that are part of learning resources (e.g. Quiz), eduQuestionType indicates the format of question being given. Example: "Multiple choice", "Open ended", "Flashcard".

additionalType.name: additionalType
additionalType.description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. Typically the value is a URI-identified RDF class, and in this case corresponds to the use of rdf:type in RDF. Text values can be used sparingly, for cases where useful information can be added without their being an appropriate schema to reference. In the case of text values, the class label should follow the schema.org style guide.

broadcastChannelId.name: broadcastChannelId
broadcastChannelId.description: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

yearBuilt.name: yearBuilt
yearBuilt.description: The year an [[Accommodation]] was constructed. This corresponds to the [YearBuilt field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/YearBuilt+Field).

partOfSeason.name: partOfSeason
partOfSeason.description: The season to which this episode belongs.

broadcastSignalModulation.name: broadcastSignalModulation
broadcastSignalModulation.description: The modulation (e.g. FM, AM, etc) used by a particular broadcast service.

programName.name: programName
programName.description: The program providing the membership. It is preferable to use [:program](https://schema.org/program) instead.

providerMobility.name: providerMobility
providerMobility.description: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

amountOfThisGood.name: amountOfThisGood
amountOfThisGood.description: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

actionProcess.name: actionProcess
actionProcess.description: Description of the process by which the action was performed.

diversityStaffingReport.name: diversityStaffingReport
diversityStaffingReport.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

legislationTransposes.name: legislationTransposes
legislationTransposes.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of legislation) fulfills the objectives set by another legislation, by passing appropriate implementation measures. Typically, some legislations of European Union's member states or regions transpose European Directives. This indicates a legally binding link between the 2 legislations.

sourcedFrom.name: sourcedFrom
sourcedFrom.description: The neurological pathway that originates the neurons.

paymentStatus.name: paymentStatus
paymentStatus.description: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

requiredCollateral.name: requiredCollateral
requiredCollateral.description: Assets required to secure loan or credit repayments. It may take form of third party pledge, goods, financial instruments (cash, securities, etc.)

financialAidEligible.name: financialAidEligible
financialAidEligible.description: A financial aid type or program which students may use to pay for tuition or fees associated with the program.

itinerary.name: itinerary
itinerary.description: Destination(s) ( [[Place]] ) that make up a trip. For a trip where destination order is important use [[ItemList]] to specify that order (see examples).

addOn.name: addOn
addOn.description: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

baseSalary.name: baseSalary
baseSalary.description: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

evidenceOrigin.name: evidenceOrigin
evidenceOrigin.description: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

foodEstablishment.name: foodEstablishment
foodEstablishment.description: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

byArtist.name: byArtist
byArtist.description: The artist that performed this album or recording.

algorithm.name: algorithm
algorithm.description: The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.

numberOfPartialBathrooms.name: numberOfPartialBathrooms
numberOfPartialBathrooms.description: Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and  bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsPartial field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsPartial+Field).

orderPercentage.name: orderPercentage
orderPercentage.description: Value in the range [0.0 ; 1.0] representing the fraction of the value of the order that is charged as shipping cost.

hasMolecularFunction.name: hasMolecularFunction
hasMolecularFunction.description: Molecular function performed by this BioChemEntity; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

pickupLocation.name: pickupLocation
pickupLocation.description: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

payload.name: payload
payload.description:
The permitted weight of passengers and cargo, EXCLUDING the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: Many databases specify the permitted TOTAL weight instead, which is the sum of [[weight]] and [[payload]]
* Note 2: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 3: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 4: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

startTime.name: startTime
startTime.description: The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

isrcCode.name: isrcCode
isrcCode.description: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

applicableCountry.name: applicableCountry
applicableCountry.description: A country where a particular merchant return policy applies to, for example the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

isRelatedTo.name: isRelatedTo
isRelatedTo.description: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

clipNumber.name: clipNumber
clipNumber.description: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

colorist.name: colorist
colorist.description: The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

keywords.name: keywords
keywords.description: Keywords or tags used to describe some item. Multiple textual entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas, or by repeating the property.

healthPlanCoinsuranceOption.name: healthPlanCoinsuranceOption
healthPlanCoinsuranceOption.description: Whether the coinsurance applies before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

priceCurrency.name: priceCurrency
priceCurrency.description: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

track.name: track
track.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

legislationType.name: legislationType
legislationType.description: The type of the legislation. Examples of values are "law", "act", "directive", "decree", "regulation", "statutory instrument", "loi organique", "rglement grand-ducal", etc., depending on the country.

serviceSmsNumber.name: serviceSmsNumber
serviceSmsNumber.description: The number to access the service by text message.

interactionService.name: interactionService
interactionService.description: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

slogan.name: slogan
slogan.description: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

broadcastTimezone.name: broadcastTimezone
broadcastTimezone.description: The timezone in [ISO 8601 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) for which the service bases its broadcasts.

educationalProgramMode.name: educationalProgramMode
educationalProgramMode.description: Similar to courseMode, the medium or means of delivery of the program as a whole. The value may either be a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

priceType.name: priceType
priceType.description: Defines the type of a price specified for an offered product, for example a list price, a (temporary) sale price or a manufacturer suggested retail price. If multiple prices are specified for an offer the [[priceType]] property can be used to identify the type of each such specified price. The value of priceType can be specified as a value from enumeration PriceTypeEnumeration or, a UN/EDIFACT 5387 code, or as a free form text string for price types that are not already predefined in PriceTypeEnumeration.

labelDetails.name: labelDetails
labelDetails.description: Link to the drug's label details.

endDate.name: endDate
endDate.description: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

requiredQuantity.name: requiredQuantity
requiredQuantity.description: The required quantity of the item(s).

eventAttendanceMode.name: eventAttendanceMode
eventAttendanceMode.description: The eventAttendanceMode of an event indicates whether it occurs online, offline, or a mix.

seatSection.name: seatSection
seatSection.description: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

hasPart.name: hasPart
hasPart.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

transitTime.name: transitTime
transitTime.description: The typical delay the order has been sent for delivery and the goods reach the final customer. In the context of [[ShippingDeliveryTime]], use the [[QuantitativeValue]]. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY). In the context of [[ShippingConditions]], use the [[ServicePeriod]]. It has a duration (as a [[QuantitativeValue]]) and also business days and a cut-off time.

floorSize.name: floorSize
floorSize.description: The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot. Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard.

totalJobOpenings.name: totalJobOpenings
totalJobOpenings.description: The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

funder.name: funder
funder.description: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

publishedOn.name: publishedOn
publishedOn.description: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

accessMode.name: accessMode
accessMode.description: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessMode-vocabulary).

appearance.name: appearance
appearance.description: Indicates an occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

seasonNumber.name: seasonNumber
seasonNumber.description: Position of the season within an ordered group of seasons.

cvdCollectionDate.name: cvdCollectionDate
cvdCollectionDate.description: collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

deliveryLeadTime.name: deliveryLeadTime
deliveryLeadTime.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

returnMethod.name: returnMethod
returnMethod.description: The type of return method offered, specified from an enumeration.

representativeOfPage.name: representativeOfPage
representativeOfPage.description: Indicates whether this image is representative of the content of the page.

incomeLimit.name: incomeLimit
incomeLimit.description: Optional. Income limit for which the incentive is applicable for. If MonetaryAmount is specified, this should be based on annualized income (e.g. if an incentive is limited to those making { "@type": "MonetaryAmount", "maxValue": 114000, "currency": "USD", } Use Text for incentives that are limited based on other criteria, for example if an incentive is only available to recipients making 120% of the median poverty income in their area.

printColumn.name: printColumn
printColumn.description: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

inChI.name: inChI
inChI.description: Non-proprietary identifier for molecular entity that can be used in printed and electronic data sources thus enabling easier linking of diverse data compilations.

toRecipient.name: toRecipient
toRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient who was directly sent the message.

issueNumber.name: issueNumber
issueNumber.description: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

pageEnd.name: pageEnd
pageEnd.description: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

productID.name: productID
productID.description: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.

realEstateAgent.name: realEstateAgent
realEstateAgent.description: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

usesDevice.name: usesDevice
usesDevice.description: Device used to perform the test.

legislationDateOfApplicability.name: legislationDateOfApplicability
legislationDateOfApplicability.description: The date at which the Legislation becomes applicable. This can sometimes be distinct from the date of entry into force : a text may come in force today, and state it will become applicable in 3 months.

countryOfLastProcessing.name: countryOfLastProcessing
countryOfLastProcessing.description: The place where the item (typically [[Product]]) was last processed and tested before importation.

duringMedia.name: duringMedia
duringMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

providesService.name: providesService
providesService.description: The service provided by this channel.

mobileUrl.name: mobileUrl
mobileUrl.description: The [[mobileUrl]] property is provided for specific situations in which data consumers need to determine whether one of several provided URLs is a dedicated 'mobile site'. To discourage over-use, and reflecting intial usecases, the property is expected only on [[Product]] and [[Offer]], rather than [[Thing]]. The general trend in web technology is towards [responsive design](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsive_web_design) in which content can be flexibly adapted to a wide range of browsing environments. Pages and sites referenced with the long-established [[url]] property should ideally also be usable on a wide variety of devices, including mobile phones. In most cases, it would be pointless and counter productive to attempt to update all [[url]] markup to use [[mobileUrl]] for more mobile-oriented pages. The property is intended for the case when items (primarily [[Product]] and [[Offer]]) have extra URLs hosted on an additional "mobile site" alongside the main one. It should not be taken as an endorsement of this publication style.

actor.name: actor
actor.description: An actor (individual or a group), e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

geo.name: geo
geo.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity.name: maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity
maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity.description: The maximum virtual attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OnlineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the online aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

constraintProperty.name: constraintProperty
constraintProperty.description: Indicates a property used as a constraint. For example, in the definition of a [[StatisticalVariable]]. The value is a property, either from within Schema.org or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

aggregateRating.name: aggregateRating
aggregateRating.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

isPlanForApartment.name: isPlanForApartment
isPlanForApartment.description: Indicates some accommodation that this floor plan describes.

cause.name: cause
cause.description: The cause of a medical condition.

postalCodeRange.name: postalCodeRange
postalCodeRange.description: A defined range of postal codes.

statType.name: statType
statType.description: Indicates the kind of statistic represented by a [[StatisticalVariable]], e.g. mean, count etc. The value of statType is a property, either from within Schema.org (e.g. [[median]], [[marginOfError]], [[maxValue]], [[minValue]]) or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

prepTime.name: prepTime
prepTime.description: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

itemReviewed.name: itemReviewed
itemReviewed.description: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

itemDefectReturnLabelSource.name: itemDefectReturnLabelSource
itemDefectReturnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a defect product.

holdingArchive.name: holdingArchive
holdingArchive.description: [[ArchiveOrganization]] that holds, keeps or maintains the [[ArchiveComponent]].

smiles.name: smiles
smiles.description: A specification in form of a line notation for describing the structure of chemical species using short ASCII strings. Double bond stereochemistry \ indicators may need to be escaped in the string in formats where the backslash is an escape character.

eligibilityToWorkRequirement.name: eligibilityToWorkRequirement
eligibilityToWorkRequirement.description: The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

measurementTechnique.name: measurementTechnique
measurementTechnique.description: A technique, method or technology used in an [[Observation]], [[StatisticalVariable]] or [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (for datasets, described using [[variableMeasured]]; for [[Observation]], a [[StatisticalVariable]]). Often but not necessarily each [[variableMeasured]] will have an explicit representation as (or mapping to) an property such as those defined in Schema.org, or other RDF vocabularies and "knowledge graphs". In that case the subproperty of [[variableMeasured]] called [[measuredProperty]] is applicable. The [[measurementTechnique]] property helps when extra clarification is needed about how a [[measuredProperty]] was measured. This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but can often serve as a high level summary for dataset discovery. For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence". If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory". If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]]. The value can also be from an enumeration, organized as a [[MeasurementMetholdEnumeration]].

strengthValue.name: strengthValue
strengthValue.description: The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

relatedTherapy.name: relatedTherapy
relatedTherapy.description: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

jobStartDate.name: jobStartDate
jobStartDate.description: The date on which a successful applicant for this job would be expected to start work. Choose a specific date in the future or use the jobImmediateStart property to indicate the position is to be filled as soon as possible.

material.name: material
material.description: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

candidate.name: candidate
candidate.description: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

accessibilityControl.name: accessibilityControl
accessibilityControl.description: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityControl-vocabulary).

arterialBranch.name: arterialBranch
arterialBranch.description: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

numberOfSeasons.name: numberOfSeasons
numberOfSeasons.description: The number of seasons in this series.

recordedAt.name: recordedAt
recordedAt.description: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

studyDesign.name: studyDesign
studyDesign.description: Specifics about the observational study design (enumerated).

bankAccountType.name: bankAccountType
bankAccountType.description: The type of a bank account.

trainNumber.name: trainNumber
trainNumber.description: The unique identifier for the train.

authenticator.name: authenticator
authenticator.description: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

serviceOutput.name: serviceOutput
serviceOutput.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

productSupported.name: productSupported
productSupported.description: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

rangeIncludes.name: rangeIncludes
rangeIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that constitutes (one of) the expected type(s) for values of the property.

recipeInstructions.name: recipeInstructions
recipeInstructions.description: A step in making the recipe, in the form of a single item (document, video, etc.) or an ordered list with HowToStep and/or HowToSection items.

bed.name: bed
bed.description: The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text. If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

accelerationTime.name: accelerationTime
accelerationTime.description:
The time needed to accelerate the vehicle from a given start velocity to a given target velocity.

Typical unit code(s): SEC for seconds

* Note: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]], or use [[valueReference]] with a [[QuantitativeValue]] of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.

merchantReturnDays.name: merchantReturnDays
merchantReturnDays.description: Specifies either a fixed return date or the number of days (from the delivery date) that a product can be returned. Used when the [[returnPolicyCategory]] property is specified as [[MerchantReturnFiniteReturnWindow]].

successorOf.name: successorOf
successorOf.description: A pointer from a newer variant of a product to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

applicationStartDate.name: applicationStartDate
applicationStartDate.description: The date at which the program begins collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

countryOfAssembly.name: countryOfAssembly
countryOfAssembly.description: The place where the product was assembled.

characterAttribute.name: characterAttribute
characterAttribute.description: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

coursePrerequisites.name: coursePrerequisites
coursePrerequisites.description: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another [[Course]] or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using [[AlignmentObject]].

dependencies.name: dependencies
dependencies.description: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

leiCode.name: leiCode
leiCode.description: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

loanPaymentAmount.name: loanPaymentAmount
loanPaymentAmount.description: The amount of money to pay in a single payment.

orderItemStatus.name: orderItemStatus
orderItemStatus.description: The current status of the order item.

evidenceLevel.name: evidenceLevel
evidenceLevel.description: Strength of evidence of the data used to formulate the guideline (enumerated).

knowsLanguage.name: knowsLanguage
knowsLanguage.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

maintainer.name: maintainer
maintainer.description: A maintainer of a [[Dataset]], software package ([[SoftwareApplication]]), or other [[Project]]. A maintainer is a [[Person]] or [[Organization]] that manages contributions to, and/or publication of, some (typically complex) artifact. It is common for distributions of software and data to be based on "upstream" sources. When [[maintainer]] is applied to a specific version of something e.g. a particular version or packaging of a [[Dataset]], it is always possible that the upstream source has a different maintainer. The [[isBasedOn]] property can be used to indicate such relationships between datasets to make the different maintenance roles clear. Similarly in the case of software, a package may have dedicated maintainers working on integration into software distributions such as Ubuntu, as well as upstream maintainers of the underlying work.

meetsEmissionStandard.name: meetsEmissionStandard
meetsEmissionStandard.description: Indicates that the vehicle meets the respective emission standard.

playerType.name: playerType
playerType.description: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

populationType.name: populationType
populationType.description: Indicates the populationType common to all members of a [[StatisticalPopulation]] or all cases within the scope of a [[StatisticalVariable]].

healthPlanCopayOption.name: healthPlanCopayOption
healthPlanCopayOption.description: Whether the copay is before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

timeRequired.name: timeRequired
timeRequired.description: Approximate or typical time it usually takes to work with or through the content of this work for the typical or target audience.

tool.name: tool
tool.description: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

sha256.name: sha256
sha256.description: The [SHA-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-2) SHA256 hash of the content of the item. For example, a zero-length input has value 'e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855'.

isBasedOn.name: isBasedOn
isBasedOn.description: A resource from which this work is derived or from which it is a modification or adaptation.

spokenByCharacter.name: spokenByCharacter
spokenByCharacter.description: The (e.g. fictional) character, Person or Organization to whom the quotation is attributed within the containing CreativeWork.

downvoteCount.name: downvoteCount
downvoteCount.description: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

parentService.name: parentService
parentService.description: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

partOfOrder.name: partOfOrder
partOfOrder.description: The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

warning.name: warning
warning.description: Any FDA or other warnings about the drug (text or URL).

dropoffTime.name: dropoffTime
dropoffTime.description: When a rental car can be dropped off.

legislationJurisdiction.name: legislationJurisdiction
legislationJurisdiction.description: The jurisdiction from which the legislation originates.

answerCount.name: answerCount
answerCount.description: The number of answers this question has received.

yearlyRevenue.name: yearlyRevenue
yearlyRevenue.description: The size of the business in annual revenue.

maxPrice.name: maxPrice
maxPrice.description: The highest price if the price is a range.

availableStrength.name: availableStrength
availableStrength.description: An available dosage strength for the drug.

estimatedFlightDuration.name: estimatedFlightDuration
estimatedFlightDuration.description: The estimated time the flight will take.

lodgingUnitDescription.name: lodgingUnitDescription
lodgingUnitDescription.description: A full description of the lodging unit.

playersOnline.name: playersOnline
playersOnline.description: Number of players on the server.

extendedAddress.name: extendedAddress
extendedAddress.description: An address extension such as an apartment number, C/O or alternative name.

sugarContent.name: sugarContent
sugarContent.description: The number of grams of sugar.

gtin14.name: gtin14
gtin14.description: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

tributary.name: tributary
tributary.description: The anatomical or organ system that the vein flows into; a larger structure that the vein connects to.

value.name: value
value.description:
The value of a [[QuantitativeValue]] (including [[Observation]]) or property value node.

* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
* For [[PropertyValue]], it can be 'Text', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

brand.name: brand
brand.description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

streetAddress.name: streetAddress
streetAddress.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

codeValue.name: codeValue
codeValue.description: A short textual code that uniquely identifies the value.

identifier.name: identifier
identifier.description: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of [[Thing]], such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#identifierBg) for more details.

downPayment.name: downPayment
downPayment.description: a type of payment made in cash during the onset of the purchase of an expensive good/service. The payment typically represents only a percentage of the full purchase price.

skills.name: skills
skills.description: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is either claimed by a person, an organization or desired or required to fulfill a role or to work in an occupation.

cvdNumC19MechVentPats.name: cvdNumC19MechVentPats
cvdNumC19MechVentPats.description: numc19mechventpats - HOSPITALIZED and VENTILATED: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19 and are on a mechanical ventilator.

associatedAnatomy.name: associatedAnatomy
associatedAnatomy.description: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

editEIDR.name: editEIDR
editEIDR.description: An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing a specific edit / edition for a work of film or television. For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" whose [[titleEIDR]] is "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J" has several edits, e.g. "10.5240/1F2A-E1C5-680A-14C6-E76B-I" and "10.5240/8A35-3BEE-6497-5D12-9E4F-3". Since schema.org types like [[Movie]] and [[TVEpisode]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

unsaturatedFatContent.name: unsaturatedFatContent
unsaturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of unsaturated fat.

returnFees.name: returnFees
