returnFees.description: The type of return fees for purchased products (for any return reason).

naics.name: naics
naics.description: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

firstPerformance.name: firstPerformance
firstPerformance.description: The date and place the work was first performed.

referencesOrder.name: referencesOrder
referencesOrder.description: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

departureGate.name: departureGate
departureGate.description: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

founder.name: founder
founder.description: A person or organization who founded this organization.

expectsAcceptanceOf.name: expectsAcceptanceOf
expectsAcceptanceOf.description: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

hasMerchantReturnPolicy.name: hasMerchantReturnPolicy
hasMerchantReturnPolicy.description: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

artworkSurface.name: artworkSurface
artworkSurface.description: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

parentOrganization.name: parentOrganization
parentOrganization.description: The larger organization that this organization is a [[subOrganization]] of, if any.

possibleTreatment.name: possibleTreatment
possibleTreatment.description: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

inverseOf.name: inverseOf
inverseOf.description: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

eligibleWithSupplier.name: eligibleWithSupplier
eligibleWithSupplier.description: The supplier of the incentivized item/service for which the incentive is valid for such as a utility company, merchant, or contractor.

seatingCapacity.name: seatingCapacity
seatingCapacity.description: The number of persons that can be seated (e.g. in a vehicle), both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

releaseNotes.name: releaseNotes
releaseNotes.description: Description of what changed in this version.

hasAdultConsideration.name: hasAdultConsideration
hasAdultConsideration.description: Used to tag an item to be intended or suitable for consumption or use by adults only.

exerciseType.name: exerciseType
exerciseType.description: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

broadcastFrequencyValue.name: broadcastFrequencyValue
broadcastFrequencyValue.description: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

originalMediaLink.name: originalMediaLink
originalMediaLink.description: Link to the page containing an original version of the content, or directly to an online copy of the original [[MediaObject]] content, e.g. video file.

hasMap.name: hasMap
hasMap.description: A URL to a map of the place.

orderQuantity.name: orderQuantity
orderQuantity.description: The number of the item ordered. If the property is not set, assume the quantity is one.

areaServed.name: areaServed
areaServed.description: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

artist.name: artist
artist.description: The primary artist for a work in a medium other than pencils or digital line art--for example, if the primary artwork is done in watercolors or digital paints.

object.name: object
object.description: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). E.g. John read *a book*.

comprisedOf.name: comprisedOf
comprisedOf.description: Specifying something physically contained by something else. Typically used here for the underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

customerRemorseReturnFees.name: customerRemorseReturnFees
customerRemorseReturnFees.description: The type of return fees if the product is returned due to customer remorse.

firstAppearance.name: firstAppearance
firstAppearance.description: Indicates the first known occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

globalLocationNumber.name: globalLocationNumber
globalLocationNumber.description: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

handlingTime.name: handlingTime
handlingTime.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup. In the context of [[ShippingDeliveryTime]], Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY). This is by common convention assumed to mean business days (if a unitCode is used, coded as "d"), i.e. only counting days when the business normally operates. In the context of [[ShippingService]], use the [[ServicePeriod]] format, that contains the same information in a structured form, with cut-off time, business days and duration.

proprietaryName.name: proprietaryName
proprietaryName.description: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

shippingConditions.name: shippingConditions
shippingConditions.description: The conditions (constraints, price) applicable to the [[ShippingService]].

availableDeliveryMethod.name: availableDeliveryMethod
availableDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

opponent.name: opponent
opponent.description: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

size.name: size
size.description: A standardized size of a product or creative work, specified either through a simple textual string (for example 'XL', '32Wx34L'), a QuantitativeValue with a unitCode, or a comprehensive and structured [[SizeSpecification]]; in other cases, the [[width]], [[height]], [[depth]] and [[weight]] properties may be more applicable.

courseSchedule.name: courseSchedule
courseSchedule.description: Represents the length and pace of a course, expressed as a [[Schedule]].

inventoryLevel.name: inventoryLevel
inventoryLevel.description: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

insertion.name: insertion
insertion.description: The place of attachment of a muscle, or what the muscle moves.

alignmentType.name: alignmentType
alignmentType.description: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', and 'educationalSubject'.

printEdition.name: printEdition
printEdition.description: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

membershipNumber.name: membershipNumber
membershipNumber.description: A unique identifier for the membership.

suggestedGender.name: suggestedGender
suggestedGender.description: The suggested gender of the intended person or audience, for example "male", "female", or "unisex".

valueAddedTaxIncluded.name: valueAddedTaxIncluded
valueAddedTaxIncluded.description: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

owner.name: owner
owner.description: A person or organization who owns this Thing.

hasVariant.name: hasVariant
hasVariant.description: Indicates a [[Product]] that is a member of this [[ProductGroup]] (or [[ProductModel]]).

pronouns.name: pronouns
pronouns.description: A short string listing or describing pronouns for a person. Typically the person concerned is the best authority as pronouns are a critical part of personal identity and expression. Publishers and consumers of this information are reminded to treat this data responsibly, take country-specific laws related to gender expression into account, and be wary of out-of-date data and drawing unwarranted inferences about the person being described. In English, formulations such as "they/them", "she/her", and "he/him" are commonly used online and can also be used here. We do not intend to enumerate all possible micro-syntaxes in all languages. More structured and well-defined external values for pronouns can be referenced using the [[StructuredValue]] or [[DefinedTerm]] values.

citation.name: citation
citation.description: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

courseMode.name: courseMode
courseMode.description: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous).

healthPlanNetworkId.name: healthPlanNetworkId
healthPlanNetworkId.description: Name or unique ID of network. (Networks are often reused across different insurance plans.)

event.name: event
event.description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

phoneticText.name: phoneticText
phoneticText.description: Representation of a text [[textValue]] using the specified [[speechToTextMarkup]]. For example the city name of Houston in IPA: /hjustn/.

returnShippingFeesAmount.name: returnShippingFeesAmount
returnShippingFeesAmount.description: Amount of shipping costs for product returns (for any reason). Applicable when property [[returnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

governmentBenefitsInfo.name: governmentBenefitsInfo
governmentBenefitsInfo.description: governmentBenefitsInfo provides information about government benefits associated with a SpecialAnnouncement.

addressRegion.name: addressRegion
addressRegion.description: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country).

broadcastSubChannel.name: broadcastSubChannel
broadcastSubChannel.description: The subchannel used for the broadcast.

numberOfDoors.name: numberOfDoors
numberOfDoors.description: The number of doors.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

employerOverview.name: employerOverview
employerOverview.description: A description of the employer, career opportunities and work environment for this position.

affiliation.name: affiliation
affiliation.description: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

interactionStatistic.name: interactionStatistic
interactionStatistic.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

acceptsReservations.name: acceptsReservations
acceptsReservations.description: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings ```Yes``` or ```No```.

workExample.name: workExample
workExample.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. E.g. the paperback edition, first edition, or e-book.

touristType.name: touristType
touristType.description: Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. E.g. children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

certificationStatus.name: certificationStatus
certificationStatus.description: Indicates the current status of a certification: active or inactive. See also [gs1:certificationStatus](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationStatus).

xpath.name: xpath
xpath.description: An XPath, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

closes.name: closes
closes.description: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

uploadDate.name: uploadDate
uploadDate.description: Date (including time if available) when this media object was uploaded to this site.

cvdNumICUBeds.name: cvdNumICUBeds
cvdNumICUBeds.description: numicubeds - ICU BEDS: Total number of staffed inpatient intensive care unit (ICU) beds.

iataCode.name: iataCode
iataCode.description: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

gtin8.name: gtin8
gtin8.description: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

nutrition.name: nutrition
nutrition.description: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

typeOfGood.name: typeOfGood
typeOfGood.description: The product that this structured value is referring to.

possibleComplication.name: possibleComplication
possibleComplication.description: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

webFeed.name: webFeed
webFeed.description: The URL for a feed, e.g. associated with a podcast series, blog, or series of date-stamped updates. This is usually RSS or Atom.

supersededBy.name: supersededBy
supersededBy.description: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

sku.name: sku
sku.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

isLiveBroadcast.name: isLiveBroadcast
isLiveBroadcast.description: True if the broadcast is of a live event.

maxValue.name: maxValue
maxValue.description: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

tourBookingPage.name: tourBookingPage
tourBookingPage.description: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

artform.name: artform
artform.description: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

unitCode.name: unitCode
unitCode.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

materialExtent.name: materialExtent
materialExtent.description: The quantity of the materials being described or an expression of the physical space they occupy.

softwareRequirements.name: softwareRequirements
softwareRequirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

superEvent.name: superEvent
superEvent.description: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

expectedArrivalFrom.name: expectedArrivalFrom
expectedArrivalFrom.description: The earliest date the package may arrive.

domainIncludes.name: domainIncludes
domainIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

distinguishingSign.name: distinguishingSign
distinguishingSign.description: One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

ccRecipient.name: ccRecipient
ccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

measurementMethod.name: measurementMethod
measurementMethod.description: A subproperty of [[measurementTechnique]] that can be used for specifying specific methods, in particular via [[MeasurementMethodEnum]].

employmentUnit.name: employmentUnit
employmentUnit.description: Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

recordLabel.name: recordLabel
recordLabel.description: The label that issued the release.

legalName.name: legalName
legalName.description: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

recipeIngredient.name: recipeIngredient
recipeIngredient.description: An ingredient or ordered list of ingredients and potentially quantities used in the recipe, e.g. 1 cup of sugar, flour or garlic. The ingredients can be represented as free text or more structured values.

category.name: category
category.description: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

healthCondition.name: healthCondition
healthCondition.description: Specifying the health condition(s) of a patient, medical study, or other target audience.

membershipPointsEarned.name: membershipPointsEarned
membershipPointsEarned.description: The number of membership points earned by the member. If necessary, the unitText can be used to express the units the points are issued in. (E.g. stars, miles, etc.)

follows.name: follows
follows.description: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

lesserOrEqual.name: lesserOrEqual
lesserOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

beneficiaryBank.name: beneficiaryBank
beneficiaryBank.description: A bank or banks branch, financial institution or international financial institution operating the beneficiarys bank account or releasing funds for the beneficiary.

tocContinuation.name: tocContinuation
tocContinuation.description: A [[HyperTocEntry]] can have a [[tocContinuation]] indicated, which is another [[HyperTocEntry]] that would be the default next item to play or render.

certificationRating.name: certificationRating
certificationRating.description: Rating of a certification instance (as defined by an independent certification body). Typically this rating can be used to rate the level to which the requirements of the certification instance are fulfilled. See also [gs1:certificationValue](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationValue).

prescribingInfo.name: prescribingInfo
prescribingInfo.description: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

hasTierBenefit.name: hasTierBenefit
hasTierBenefit.description: A member benefit for a particular tier of a loyalty program.

measurementDenominator.name: measurementDenominator
measurementDenominator.description: Identifies the denominator variable when an observation represents a ratio or percentage.

isTierOf.name: isTierOf
isTierOf.description: The member program this tier is a part of.

spatial.name: spatial
spatial.description: The "spatial" property can be used in cases when more specific properties (e.g. [[locationCreated]], [[spatialCoverage]], [[contentLocation]]) are not known to be appropriate.

valueReference.name: valueReference
valueReference.description: A secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature or a type of measurement.

carrierRequirements.name: carrierRequirements
carrierRequirements.description: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).

molecularFormula.name: molecularFormula
molecularFormula.description: The empirical formula is the simplest whole number ratio of all the atoms in a molecule.

reviewCount.name: reviewCount
reviewCount.description: The count of total number of reviews.

cookingMethod.name: cookingMethod
cookingMethod.description: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

courseWorkload.name: courseWorkload
courseWorkload.description: The amount of work expected of students taking the course, often provided as a figure per week or per month, and may be broken down by type. For example, "2 hours of lectures, 1 hour of lab work and 3 hours of independent study per week".

associatedClaimReview.name: associatedClaimReview
associatedClaimReview.description: An associated [[ClaimReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

releaseOf.name: releaseOf
releaseOf.description: The album this is a release of.

videoFormat.name: videoFormat
videoFormat.description: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

homeTeam.name: homeTeam
homeTeam.description: The home team in a sports event.

cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats.name: cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats
cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats.description: numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

parentTaxon.name: parentTaxon
parentTaxon.description: Closest parent taxon of the taxon in question.

elevation.name: elevation
elevation.description: The elevation of a location ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNIT\_OF\_MEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

gtin13.name: gtin13
gtin13.description: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

subTrip.name: subTrip
subTrip.description: Identifies a [[Trip]] that is a subTrip of this Trip. For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

producer.name: producer
producer.description: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, TV/radio series etc.).

audienceType.name: audienceType
audienceType.description: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

cvdNumC19HOPats.name: cvdNumC19HOPats
cvdNumC19HOPats.description: numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

procedureType.name: procedureType
procedureType.description: The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

vehicleSpecialUsage.name: vehicleSpecialUsage
vehicleSpecialUsage.description: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

safetyConsideration.name: safetyConsideration
safetyConsideration.description: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

offers.name: offers
offers.description: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

departureBoatTerminal.name: departureBoatTerminal
departureBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat departs.

mentions.name: mentions
mentions.description: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

vehicleSeatingCapacity.name: vehicleSeatingCapacity
vehicleSeatingCapacity.description: The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

signDetected.name: signDetected
signDetected.description: A sign detected by the test.

acceptedOffer.name: acceptedOffer
acceptedOffer.description: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

costPerUnit.name: costPerUnit
costPerUnit.description: The cost per unit of the drug.

servicePhone.name: servicePhone
servicePhone.description: The phone number to use to access the service.

workload.name: workload
workload.description: Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

loanPaymentFrequency.name: loanPaymentFrequency
loanPaymentFrequency.description: Frequency of payments due, i.e. number of months between payments. This is defined as a frequency, i.e. the reciprocal of a period of time.

valueName.name: valueName
valueName.description: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

timeToComplete.name: timeToComplete
timeToComplete.description: The expected length of time to complete the program if attending full-time.

customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount.name: customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount
customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount.description: The amount of shipping costs if a product is returned due to customer remorse. Applicable when property [[customerRemorseReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

seasonalOverride.name: seasonalOverride
seasonalOverride.description: Limited period during which these shipping conditions apply.

domiciledMortgage.name: domiciledMortgage
domiciledMortgage.description: Whether borrower is a resident of the jurisdiction where the property is located.

study.name: study
study.description: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

lowPrice.name: lowPrice
lowPrice.description:
The lowest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

isFamilyFriendly.name: isFamilyFriendly
isFamilyFriendly.description: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

referenceQuantity.name: referenceQuantity
referenceQuantity.description: The reference quantity for which a certain price applies, e.g. 1 EUR per 4 kWh of electricity. This property is a replacement for unitOfMeasurement for the advanced cases where the price does not relate to a standard unit.

serviceUrl.name: serviceUrl
serviceUrl.description: The website to access the service.

mileageFromOdometer.name: mileageFromOdometer
mileageFromOdometer.description: The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.\n\nTypical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles.

riskFactor.name: riskFactor
riskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age, coexisting condition.

accessibilityFeature.name: accessibilityFeature
accessibilityFeature.description: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityFeature-vocabulary).

legislationLegalForce.name: legislationLegalForce
legislationLegalForce.description: Whether the legislation is currently in force, not in force, or partially in force.

monthsOfExperience.name: monthsOfExperience
monthsOfExperience.description: Indicates the minimal number of months of experience required for a position.

secondaryPrevention.name: secondaryPrevention
secondaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

addressLocality.name: addressLocality
addressLocality.description: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

jobImmediateStart.name: jobImmediateStart
jobImmediateStart.description: An indicator as to whether a position is available for an immediate start.

claimReviewed.name: claimReviewed
claimReviewed.description: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

step.name: step
step.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

containsPlace.name: containsPlace
containsPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

memberOf.name: memberOf
memberOf.description: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

suggestedAnswer.name: suggestedAnswer
suggestedAnswer.description: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

bookingTime.name: bookingTime
bookingTime.description: The date and time the reservation was booked.

gameServer.name: gameServer
gameServer.description: The server on which it is possible to play the game.

videoFrameSize.name: videoFrameSize
videoFrameSize.description: The frame size of the video.

code.name: code
code.description: A medical code for the entity, taken from a controlled vocabulary or ontology such as ICD-9, DiseasesDB, MeSH, SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, etc.

dateIssued.name: dateIssued
dateIssued.description: The date the ticket was issued.

version.name: version
version.description: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

availableFrom.name: availableFrom
availableFrom.description: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

employmentType.name: employmentType
employmentType.description: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

actionableFeedbackPolicy.name: actionableFeedbackPolicy
actionableFeedbackPolicy.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsrooms), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

floorLimit.name: floorLimit
floorLimit.description: A floor limit is the amount of money above which credit card transactions must be authorized.

numberOfBeds.name: numberOfBeds
numberOfBeds.description: The quantity of the given bed type available in the HotelRoom, Suite, House, or Apartment.

purchaseDate.name: purchaseDate
purchaseDate.description: The date the item, e.g. vehicle, was purchased by the current owner.

originalMediaContextDescription.name: originalMediaContextDescription
originalMediaContextDescription.description: Describes, in a [[MediaReview]] when dealing with [[DecontextualizedContent]], background information that can contribute to better interpretation of the [[MediaObject]].

multipleValues.name: multipleValues
multipleValues.description: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property. Default is false.

contactlessPayment.name: contactlessPayment
contactlessPayment.description: A secure method for consumers to purchase products or services via debit, credit or smartcards by using RFID or NFC technology.

recordedIn.name: recordedIn
recordedIn.description: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

flightNumber.name: flightNumber
flightNumber.description: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount.name: itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount
itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount.description: Amount of shipping costs for defect product returns. Applicable when property [[itemDefectReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

remainingAttendeeCapacity.name: remainingAttendeeCapacity
remainingAttendeeCapacity.description: The number of attendee places for an event that remain unallocated.

hasTiers.name: hasTiers
hasTiers.description: The tiers of a member program.

ineligibleRegion.name: ineligibleRegion
ineligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

blogPost.name: blogPost
blogPost.description: A posting that is part of this blog.

arrivalBoatTerminal.name: arrivalBoatTerminal
arrivalBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat arrives.

permittedUsage.name: permittedUsage
permittedUsage.description: Indications regarding the permitted usage of the accommodation.

hasEnergyConsumptionDetails.name: hasEnergyConsumptionDetails
hasEnergyConsumptionDetails.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (also known as "class" or "rating") for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

endorsers.name: endorsers
endorsers.description: People or organizations that endorse the plan.

purchaseType.name: purchaseType
purchaseType.description: Optional. The type of purchase the consumer must make in order to qualify for this incentive.

operatingSystem.name: operatingSystem
operatingSystem.description: Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OS X 10.6, Android 1.6).

referee.name: referee
referee.description: An official who watches a game or match closely to enforce the rules and arbitrate on matters arising from the play such as referees, umpires or judges. The name of the effective function can vary according to the sport.

applicationDeadline.name: applicationDeadline
applicationDeadline.description: The date on which the program stops collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle. Flexible application deadlines (for example, a program with rolling admissions) can be described in a textual string, rather than as a DateTime.

gameEdition.name: gameEdition
gameEdition.description: The edition of a video game.

relatedAnatomy.name: relatedAnatomy
relatedAnatomy.description: Anatomical systems or structures that relate to the superficial anatomy.

permissionType.name: permissionType
permissionType.description: The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

replacer.name: replacer
replacer.description: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

associatedDisease.name: associatedDisease
associatedDisease.description: Disease associated to this BioChemEntity. Such disease can be a MedicalCondition or a URL. If you want to add an evidence supporting the association, please use PropertyValue.

hospitalAffiliation.name: hospitalAffiliation
hospitalAffiliation.description: A hospital with which the physician or office is affiliated.

accountId.name: accountId
accountId.description: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

availableOnDevice.name: availableOnDevice
availableOnDevice.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

embedUrl.name: embedUrl
embedUrl.description: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the ```src``` element of an ```embed``` tag and should not be the same as the content of the ```loc``` tag.

workPerformed.name: workPerformed
workPerformed.description: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

opens.name: opens
opens.description: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

musicArrangement.name: musicArrangement
musicArrangement.description: An arrangement derived from the composition.

postOp.name: postOp
postOp.description: A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

feesAndCommissionsSpecification.name: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
feesAndCommissionsSpecification.description: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

author.name: author
author.description: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

actionOption.name: actionOption
actionOption.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

item.name: item
item.description: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').

postOfficeBoxNumber.name: postOfficeBoxNumber
postOfficeBoxNumber.description: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

hasBioPolymerSequence.name: hasBioPolymerSequence
hasBioPolymerSequence.description: A symbolic representation of a BioChemEntity. For example, a nucleotide sequence of a Gene or an amino acid sequence of a Protein.

requiredMinAge.name: requiredMinAge
requiredMinAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

validFrom.name: validFrom
validFrom.description: The date when the item becomes valid.

userInteractionCount.name: userInteractionCount
userInteractionCount.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

attendee.name: attendee
attendee.description: A person or organization attending the event.

nerve.name: nerve
nerve.description: The underlying innervation associated with the muscle.

contentRating.name: contentRating
contentRating.description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example, 'MPAA PG-13'.

subStructure.name: subStructure
subStructure.description: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

passengerPriorityStatus.name: passengerPriorityStatus
passengerPriorityStatus.description: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

priceComponent.name: priceComponent
priceComponent.description: This property links to all [[UnitPriceSpecification]] nodes that apply in parallel for the [[CompoundPriceSpecification]] node.

postalCodeBegin.name: postalCodeBegin
postalCodeBegin.description: First postal code in a range (included).

incentiveCompensation.name: incentiveCompensation
incentiveCompensation.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

fuelCapacity.name: fuelCapacity
fuelCapacity.description: The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.\n\nTypical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).

leaseLength.name: leaseLength
leaseLength.description: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

trailerWeight.name: trailerWeight
trailerWeight.description:
The permitted weight of a trailer attached to the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound
* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

hasBioChemEntityPart.name: hasBioChemEntityPart
hasBioChemEntityPart.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that (in some sense) has this BioChemEntity as a part.

contactPoint.name: contactPoint
contactPoint.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

drainsTo.name: drainsTo
drainsTo.description: The vasculature that the vein drains into.

positiveNotes.name: positiveNotes
positiveNotes.description: Provides positive considerations regarding something, for example product highlights or (alongside [[negativeNotes]]) pro/con lists for reviews. In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described. The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most positive is at the beginning of the list).

containedInPlace.name: containedInPlace
containedInPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

accommodationCategory.name: accommodationCategory
accommodationCategory.description: Category of an [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions, e.g. RESO (see [PropertySubType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertySubType+Field), and [PropertyType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertyType+Field) fields for suggested values).

dateline.name: dateline
dateline.description: A [dateline](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dateline) is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided. Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using [[locationCreated]] (which represents where a work was created, e.g. where a news report was written). For location depicted or described in the content, use [[contentLocation]]. Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

competencyRequired.name: competencyRequired
competencyRequired.description: Knowledge, skill, ability or personal attribute that must be demonstrated by a person or other entity in order to do something such as earn an Educational Occupational Credential or understand a LearningResource.

iupacName.name: iupacName
iupacName.description: Systematic method of naming chemical compounds as recommended by the International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC).

actionStatus.name: actionStatus
actionStatus.description: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

dosageForm.name: dosageForm
dosageForm.description: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

reviewAspect.name: reviewAspect
reviewAspect.description: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

typeOfBed.name: typeOfBed
typeOfBed.description: The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

processingTime.name: processingTime
processingTime.description: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

subjectOf.name: subjectOf
subjectOf.description: A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.

foodEvent.name: foodEvent
foodEvent.description: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

relatedDrug.name: relatedDrug
relatedDrug.description: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

encodesBioChemEntity.name: encodesBioChemEntity
encodesBioChemEntity.description: Another BioChemEntity encoded by this one.

naturalProgression.name: naturalProgression
naturalProgression.description: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

healthPlanCostSharing.name: healthPlanCostSharing
healthPlanCostSharing.description: The costs to the patient for services under this network or formulary.

significance.name: significance
significance.description: The significance associated with the superficial anatomy; as an example, how characteristics of the superficial anatomy can suggest underlying medical conditions or courses of treatment.

lodgingUnitType.name: lodgingUnitType
lodgingUnitType.description: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

trainingSalary.name: trainingSalary
trainingSalary.description: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

recourseLoan.name: recourseLoan
recourseLoan.description: The only way you get the money back in the event of default is the security. Recourse is where you still have the opportunity to go back to the borrower for the rest of the money.

eligibleCustomerType.name: eligibleCustomerType
eligibleCustomerType.description: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

sdLicense.name: sdLicense
sdLicense.description: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

shippingDestination.name: shippingDestination
shippingDestination.description: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways, e.g. postalCode ranges.

isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess.name: isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess
isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess.description: Biological process this BioChemEntity is involved in; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

incentivizedItem.name: incentivizedItem
incentivizedItem.description: The type or specific product(s) and/or service(s) being incentivized. DefinedTermSets are used for product and service categories such as the United Nations Standard Products and Services Code: { "@type": "DefinedTerm", "inDefinedTermSet": "https://www.unspsc.org/", "termCode": "261315XX", "name": "Photovoltaic module" } For a specific product or service, use the Product type: { "@type": "Product", "name": "Kenmore White 17" Microwave", } For multiple different incentivized items, use multiple [[DefinedTerm]] or [[Product]].

programmingModel.name: programmingModel
programmingModel.description: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

contentReferenceTime.name: contentReferenceTime
contentReferenceTime.description: The specific time described by a creative work, for works (e.g. articles, video objects etc.) that emphasise a particular moment within an Event.

agent.name: agent
agent.description: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). E.g. *John* wrote a book.

recognizedBy.name: recognizedBy
recognizedBy.description: An organization that acknowledges the validity, value or utility of a credential. Note: recognition may include a process of quality assurance or accreditation.

validForMemberTier.name: validForMemberTier
validForMemberTier.description: The membership program tier an Offer (or a PriceSpecification, OfferShippingDetails, or MerchantReturnPolicy under an Offer) is valid for.

contentLocation.name: contentLocation
contentLocation.description: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

hasBroadcastChannel.name: hasBroadcastChannel
hasBroadcastChannel.description: A broadcast channel of a broadcast service.

accountOverdraftLimit.name: accountOverdraftLimit
accountOverdraftLimit.description: An overdraft is an extension of credit from a lending institution when an account reaches zero. An overdraft allows the individual to continue withdrawing money even if the account has no funds in it. Basically the bank allows people to borrow a set amount of money.

colorSwatch.name: colorSwatch
colorSwatch.description: A color swatch image, visualizing the color of a [[Product]]. Should match the textual description specified in the [[color]] property. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

educationalFramework.name: educationalFramework
educationalFramework.description: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

dateReceived.name: dateReceived
dateReceived.description: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

sodiumContent.name: sodiumContent
sodiumContent.description: The number of milligrams of sodium.

caption.name: caption
caption.description: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the [[encodingFormat]].

quarantineGuidelines.name: quarantineGuidelines
quarantineGuidelines.description: Guidelines about quarantine rules, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

codeRepository.name: codeRepository
codeRepository.description: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, GitHub, CodePlex).

modelDate.name: modelDate
modelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

priceComponentType.name: priceComponentType
priceComponentType.description: Identifies a price component (for example, a line item on an invoice), part of the total price for an offer.

datePublished.name: datePublished
datePublished.description: Date of first publication or broadcast. For example the date a [[CreativeWork]] was broadcast or a [[Certification]] was issued.

arrivalPlatform.name: arrivalPlatform
arrivalPlatform.description: The platform where the train arrives.

sdPublisher.name: sdPublisher
sdPublisher.description: Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The [[sdPublisher]] property helps make such practices more explicit.

openingHours.name: openingHours
openingHours.description:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

* Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: ```Mo```, ```Tu```, ```We```, ```Th```, ```Fr```, ```Sa```, ```Su```.
* Times are specified using 24:00 format. For example, 3pm is specified as ```15:00```, 10am as ```10:00```. 
* Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
* If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

tongueWeight.name: tongueWeight
tongueWeight.description:
The permitted vertical load (TWR) of a trailer attached to the vehicle. Also referred to as Tongue Load Rating (TLR) or Vertical Load Rating (VLR).

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

occupationalCredentialAwarded.name: occupationalCredentialAwarded
occupationalCredentialAwarded.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

episode.name: episode
episode.description: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.

bioChemInteraction.name: bioChemInteraction
bioChemInteraction.description: A BioChemEntity that is known to interact with this item.

programMembershipUsed.name: programMembershipUsed
programMembershipUsed.description: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

ethicsPolicy.name: ethicsPolicy
ethicsPolicy.description: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

suitableForDiet.name: suitableForDiet
suitableForDiet.description: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

suggestedMaxAge.name: suggestedMaxAge
suggestedMaxAge.description: Maximum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

pathophysiology.name: pathophysiology
pathophysiology.description: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

identifyingTest.name: identifyingTest
identifyingTest.description: A diagnostic test that can identify this sign.

geoMidpoint.name: geoMidpoint
geoMidpoint.description: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape, e.g. GeoCircle.

numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits.name: numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits
numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits.description: Indicates the number of available accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAccommodationUnits]].

expertConsiderations.name: expertConsiderations
expertConsiderations.description: Medical expert advice related to the plan.

affectedBy.name: affectedBy
affectedBy.description: Drugs that affect the test's results.

alternativeHeadline.name: alternativeHeadline
alternativeHeadline.description: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

lyricist.name: lyricist
lyricist.description: The person who wrote the words.

permitAudience.name: permitAudience
permitAudience.description: The target audience for this permit.

repeatFrequency.name: repeatFrequency
repeatFrequency.description: Defines the frequency at which [[Event]]s will occur according to a schedule [[Schedule]]. The intervals between events should be defined as a [[Duration]] of time.

recipe.name: recipe
recipe.description: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

applicableLocation.name: applicableLocation
applicableLocation.description: The location in which the status applies.

reservationId.name: reservationId
reservationId.description: A unique identifier for the reservation.

requiredMaxAge.name: requiredMaxAge
requiredMaxAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

geoEquals.name: geoEquals
geoEquals.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM). "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship).

mechanismOfAction.name: mechanismOfAction
mechanismOfAction.description: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

rxcui.name: rxcui
rxcui.description: The RxCUI drug identifier from RXNORM.

salaryCurrency.name: salaryCurrency
salaryCurrency.description: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217)) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

ticketToken.name: ticketToken
ticketToken.description: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

hasParticipationOffer.name: hasParticipationOffer
hasParticipationOffer.description: An offer to participate in the event, for example, Call for Proposals, Call for Speakers, or Call for Performers.

grantee.name: grantee
grantee.description: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

abstract.name: abstract
abstract.description: An abstract is a short description that summarizes a [[CreativeWork]].

vehicleIdentificationNumber.name: vehicleIdentificationNumber
vehicleIdentificationNumber.description: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

orderStatus.name: orderStatus
orderStatus.description: The current status of the order.

geographicArea.name: geographicArea
geographicArea.description: The geographic area associated with the audience.

publisherImprint.name: publisherImprint
publisherImprint.description: The publishing division which published the comic.

encodingFormat.name: encodingFormat
encodingFormat.description: Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml) and [MDN reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/MIME_types)), e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc. In cases where a [[CreativeWork]] has several media type representations, [[encoding]] can be used to indicate each [[MediaObject]] alongside particular [[encodingFormat]] information. Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

inLanguage.name: inLanguage
inLanguage.description: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[availableLanguage]].

loanRepaymentForm.name: loanRepaymentForm
loanRepaymentForm.description: A form of paying back money previously borrowed from a lender. Repayment usually takes the form of periodic payments that normally include part principal plus interest in each payment.

healthPlanPharmacyCategory.name: healthPlanPharmacyCategory
healthPlanPharmacyCategory.description: The category or type of pharmacy associated with this cost sharing.

biomechnicalClass.name: biomechnicalClass
biomechnicalClass.description: The biomechanical properties of the bone.

acceptedAnswer.name: acceptedAnswer
acceptedAnswer.description: The answer(s) that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

trainName.name: trainName
trainName.description: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

accessCode.name: accessCode
accessCode.description: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

mainEntityOfPage.name: mainEntityOfPage
mainEntityOfPage.description: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#mainEntityBackground) for details.

ticketNumber.name: ticketNumber
ticketNumber.description: The unique identifier for the ticket.

arrivalStation.name: arrivalStation
arrivalStation.description: The station where the train trip ends.

dietFeatures.name: dietFeatures
dietFeatures.description: Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

layoutImage.name: layoutImage
layoutImage.description: A schematic image showing the floorplan layout.

significantLink.name: significantLink
significantLink.description: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

game.name: game
game.description: Video game which is played on this server.

dateCreated.name: dateCreated
dateCreated.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

benefitsSummaryUrl.name: benefitsSummaryUrl
benefitsSummaryUrl.description: The URL that goes directly to the summary of benefits and coverage for the specific standard plan or plan variation.

albumReleaseType.name: albumReleaseType
albumReleaseType.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

archiveHeld.name: archiveHeld
archiveHeld.description: Collection, [fonds](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fonds), or item held, kept or maintained by an [[ArchiveOrganization]].

hasCertification.name: hasCertification
hasCertification.description: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.

seller.name: seller
seller.description: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods. A seller may also be a provider.

negativeNotes.name: negativeNotes
negativeNotes.description: Provides negative considerations regarding something, most typically in pro/con lists for reviews (alongside [[positiveNotes]]). For symmetry In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described. Since product descriptions tend to emphasise positive claims, it may be relatively unusual to find [[negativeNotes]] used in this way. Nevertheless for the sake of symmetry, [[negativeNotes]] can be used on [[Product]]. The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most negative is at the beginning of the list).

increasesRiskOf.name: increasesRiskOf
increasesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.

yield.name: yield
yield.description: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.

hasDriveThroughService.name: hasDriveThroughService
hasDriveThroughService.description: Indicates whether some facility (e.g. [[FoodEstablishment]], [[CovidTestingFacility]]) offers a service that can be used by driving through in a car. In the case of [[CovidTestingFacility]] such facilities could potentially help with social distancing from other potentially-infected users.

restockingFee.name: restockingFee
restockingFee.description: Use [[MonetaryAmount]] to specify a fixed restocking fee for product returns, or use [[Number]] to specify a percentage of the product price paid by the customer.

numberOfPreviousOwners.name: numberOfPreviousOwners
numberOfPreviousOwners.description: The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

typicalCreditsPerTerm.name: typicalCreditsPerTerm
typicalCreditsPerTerm.description: The number of credits or units a full-time student would be expected to take in 1 term however 'term' is defined by the institution.

wheelbase.name: wheelbase
wheelbase.description: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels.\n\nTypical unit code(s): CMT for centimeters, MTR for meters, INH for inches, FOT for foot/feet.

legislationDateVersion.name: legislationDateVersion
legislationDateVersion.description: The point-in-time at which the provided description of the legislation is valid (e.g.: when looking at the law on the 2016-04-07 (= dateVersion), I get the consolidation of 2015-04-12 of the "National Insurance Contributions Act 2015")

fromLocation.name: fromLocation
fromLocation.description: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

additionalProperty.name: additionalProperty
additionalProperty.description: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristic of the entity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. https://schema.org/width, https://schema.org/color, https://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

broadcastServiceTier.name: broadcastServiceTier
broadcastServiceTier.description: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

numberOfEmployees.name: numberOfEmployees
numberOfEmployees.description: The number of employees in an organization, e.g. business.

renegotiableLoan.name: renegotiableLoan
renegotiableLoan.description: Whether the terms for payment of interest can be renegotiated during the life of the loan.

torque.name: torque
torque.description:
The torque (turning force) of the vehicle's engine.

Typical unit code(s): NU for newton metre (N m), F17 for pound-force per foot, or F48 for pound-force per inch

* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined (e.g. reference RPM) using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

sourceOrganization.name: sourceOrganization
sourceOrganization.description: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

runsTo.name: runsTo
runsTo.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

roleName.name: roleName
roleName.description: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

usedToDiagnose.name: usedToDiagnose
usedToDiagnose.description: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

isPartOfBioChemEntity.name: isPartOfBioChemEntity
isPartOfBioChemEntity.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that is (in some sense) a part of this BioChemEntity.

composer.name: composer
composer.description: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

monoisotopicMolecularWeight.name: monoisotopicMolecularWeight
monoisotopicMolecularWeight.description: The monoisotopic mass is the sum of the masses of the atoms in a molecule using the unbound, ground-state, rest mass of the principal (most abundant) isotope for each element instead of the isotopic average mass. Please include the units in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '770.230488 g/mol' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

targetDescription.name: targetDescription
targetDescription.description: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

expressedIn.name: expressedIn
expressedIn.description: Tissue, organ, biological sample, etc in which activity of this gene has been observed experimentally. For example brain, digestive system.

workHours.name: workHours
workHours.description: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

targetPopulation.name: targetPopulation
targetPopulation.description: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

distance.name: distance
distance.description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

availableLanguage.name: availableLanguage
availableLanguage.description: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]].

serviceType.name: serviceType
serviceType.description: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

expectedArrivalUntil.name: expectedArrivalUntil
expectedArrivalUntil.description: The latest date the package may arrive.

issuedThrough.name: issuedThrough
issuedThrough.description: The service through which the permit was granted.

appliesToDeliveryMethod.name: appliesToDeliveryMethod
appliesToDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

answerExplanation.name: answerExplanation
answerExplanation.description: A step-by-step or full explanation about Answer. Can outline how this Answer was achieved or contain more broad clarification or statement about it.

eventStatus.name: eventStatus
eventStatus.description: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

seriousAdverseOutcome.name: seriousAdverseOutcome
seriousAdverseOutcome.description: A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

subEvent.name: subEvent
subEvent.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

legislationRepeals.name: legislationRepeals
legislationRepeals.description: Another legislation that this legislation repeals (cancels, abrogates).

mainContentOfPage.name: mainContentOfPage
mainContentOfPage.description: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

followup.name: followup
followup.description: Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.

occupationalCategory.name: occupationalCategory
occupationalCategory.description: A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

paymentMethodType.name: paymentMethodType
paymentMethodType.description: The type of a payment method.

arrivalTerminal.name: arrivalTerminal
arrivalTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

preOp.name: preOp
preOp.description: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

inProductGroupWithID.name: inProductGroupWithID
inProductGroupWithID.description: Indicates the [[productGroupID]] for a [[ProductGroup]] that this product [[isVariantOf]].

securityScreening.name: securityScreening
securityScreening.description: The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

quest.name: quest
quest.description: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

learningResourceType.name: learningResourceType
learningResourceType.description: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

minValue.name: minValue
minValue.description: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

resultReview.name: resultReview
resultReview.description: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

circle.name: circle
circle.description: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

creativeWorkStatus.name: creativeWorkStatus
creativeWorkStatus.description: The status of a creative work in terms of its stage in a lifecycle. Example terms include Incomplete, Draft, Published, Obsolete. Some organizations define a set of terms for the stages of their publication lifecycle.

potentialUse.name: potentialUse
potentialUse.description: Intended use of the BioChemEntity by humans.

hasDigitalDocumentPermission.name: hasDigitalDocumentPermission
hasDigitalDocumentPermission.description: A permission related to the access to this document (e.g. permission to read or write an electronic document). For a public document, specify a grantee with an Audience with audienceType equal to "public".

audience.name: audience
audience.description: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

dayOfWeek.name: dayOfWeek
dayOfWeek.description: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

startDate.name: startDate
startDate.description: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

gettingTestedInfo.name: gettingTestedInfo
gettingTestedInfo.description: Information about getting tested (for a [[MedicalCondition]]), e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

iso6523Code.name: iso6523Code
iso6523Code.description: An organization identifier as defined in [ISO 6523(-1)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO/IEC_6523). The identifier should be in the `XXXX:YYYYYY:ZZZ` or `XXXX:YYYYYY`format. Where `XXXX` is a 4 digit _ICD_ (International Code Designator), `YYYYYY` is an _OID_ (Organization Identifier) with all formatting characters (dots, dashes, spaces) removed with a maximal length of 35 characters, and `ZZZ` is an optional OPI (Organization Part Identifier) with a maximum length of 35 characters. The various components (ICD, OID, OPI) are joined with a colon character (ASCII `0x3a`). Note that many existing organization identifiers defined as attributes like [leiCode](https://schema.org/leiCode) (`0199`), [duns](https://schema.org/duns) (`0060`) or [GLN](https://schema.org/globalLocationNumber) (`0088`) can be expressed using ISO-6523. If possible, ISO-6523 codes should be preferred to populating [vatID](https://schema.org/vatID) or [taxID](https://schema.org/taxID), as ISO identifiers are less ambiguous.

vehicleEngine.name: vehicleEngine
vehicleEngine.description: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

cvdNumC19Died.name: cvdNumC19Died
cvdNumC19Died.description: numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

breastfeedingWarning.name: breastfeedingWarning
breastfeedingWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

sharedContent.name: sharedContent
sharedContent.description: A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

typicalTest.name: typicalTest
typicalTest.description: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

auditDate.name: auditDate
auditDate.description: Date when a certification was last audited. See also [gs1:certificationAuditDate](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationAuditDate).

byDay.name: byDay
byDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the week on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. May be specified using either [[DayOfWeek]], or alternatively [[Text]] conforming to iCal's syntax for byDay recurrence rules.

guidelineDate.name: guidelineDate
guidelineDate.description: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.

birthPlace.name: birthPlace
birthPlace.description: The place where the person was born.

intensity.name: intensity
intensity.description: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.

trailer.name: trailer
trailer.description: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

supply.name: supply
supply.description: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

correctionsPolicy.name: correctionsPolicy
correctionsPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsrooms) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

locationCreated.name: locationCreated
locationCreated.description: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

returnLabelSource.name: returnLabelSource
returnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned for any reason.

fiberContent.name: fiberContent
fiberContent.description: The number of grams of fiber.

acceptedPaymentMethod.name: acceptedPaymentMethod
acceptedPaymentMethod.description: The payment method(s) that are accepted in general by an organization, or for some specific demand or offer.

broadcastFrequency.name: broadcastFrequency
broadcastFrequency.description: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges, e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequencies of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".

byMonthWeek.name: byMonthWeek
byMonthWeek.description: Defines the week(s) of the month on which a recurring Event takes place. Specified as an Integer between 1-5. For clarity, byMonthWeek is best used in conjunction with byDay to indicate concepts like the first and third Mondays of a month.

itemOffered.name: itemOffered
itemOffered.description: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

legislationEnsuresImplementationOf.name: legislationEnsuresImplementationOf
legislationEnsuresImplementationOf.description: Indicates that this Legislation ensures the implementation of another Legislation, for example by modifying national legislations so that they do not contradict to an EU regulation or decision. This implies a legal meaning. Transpositions of EU Directive should be captured with legislationTransposes.

legalStatus.name: legalStatus
legalStatus.description: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

performer.name: performer
performer.description: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

line.name: line
line.description: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

numChildren.name: numChildren
numChildren.description: The number of children staying in the unit.

transFatContent.name: transFatContent
transFatContent.description: The number of grams of trans fat.

recipient.name: recipient
recipient.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

availability.name: availability
availability.description: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

repetitions.name: repetitions
