repetitions.description: Number of times one should repeat the activity.

billingPeriod.name: billingPeriod
billingPeriod.description: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

diseaseSpreadStatistics.name: diseaseSpreadStatistics
diseaseSpreadStatistics.description: Statistical information about the spread of a disease, either as [[WebContent]], or described directly as a [[Dataset]], or the specific [[Observation]]s in the dataset. When a [[WebContent]] URL is provided, the page indicated might also contain more such markup.

workTranslation.name: workTranslation
workTranslation.description: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. E.g.  has an English workTranslation Journey to the West, a German workTranslation Monkeys Pilgerfahrt and a Vietnamese translation Ty du k bnh kho.

loanTerm.name: loanTerm
loanTerm.description: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

albumProductionType.name: albumProductionType
albumProductionType.description: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

volumeNumber.name: volumeNumber
volumeNumber.description: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

loanMortgageMandateAmount.name: loanMortgageMandateAmount
loanMortgageMandateAmount.description: Amount of mortgage mandate that can be converted into a proper mortgage at a later stage.

typicalAgeRange.name: typicalAgeRange
typicalAgeRange.description: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

returnPolicyCategory.name: returnPolicyCategory
returnPolicyCategory.description: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

isResizable.name: isResizable
isResizable.description: Whether the 3DModel allows resizing. For example, room layout applications often do not allow 3DModel elements to be resized to reflect reality.

underName.name: underName
underName.description: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

recommendationStrength.name: recommendationStrength
recommendationStrength.description: Strength of the guideline's recommendation (e.g. 'class I').

contentType.name: contentType
contentType.description: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

jobBenefits.name: jobBenefits
jobBenefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

isicV4.name: isicV4
isicV4.description: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

scheduleTimezone.name: scheduleTimezone
scheduleTimezone.description: Indicates the timezone for which the time(s) indicated in the [[Schedule]] are given. The value provided should be among those listed in the IANA Time Zone Database.

recordingOf.name: recordingOf
recordingOf.description: The composition this track is a recording of.

deliveryMethod.name: deliveryMethod
deliveryMethod.description: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

jobLocation.name: jobLocation
jobLocation.description: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

costOrigin.name: costOrigin
costOrigin.description: Additional details to capture the origin of the cost data. For example, 'Medicare Part B'.

departureAirport.name: departureAirport
departureAirport.description: The airport where the flight originates.

awayTeam.name: awayTeam
awayTeam.description: The away team in a sports event.

healthPlanCoinsuranceRate.name: healthPlanCoinsuranceRate
healthPlanCoinsuranceRate.description: The rate of coinsurance expressed as a number between 0.0 and 1.0.

departurePlatform.name: departurePlatform
departurePlatform.description: The platform from which the train departs.

bodyType.name: bodyType
bodyType.description: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).

equal.name: equal
equal.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

iswcCode.name: iswcCode
iswcCode.description: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

ownedFrom.name: ownedFrom
ownedFrom.description: The date and time of obtaining the product.

highPrice.name: highPrice
highPrice.description:
The highest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

validUntil.name: validUntil
validUntil.description: The date when the item is no longer valid.

postalCodeEnd.name: postalCodeEnd
postalCodeEnd.description: Last postal code in the range (included). Needs to be after [[postalCodeBegin]].

saturatedFatContent.name: saturatedFatContent
saturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of saturated fat.

observationAbout.name: observationAbout
observationAbout.description: The [[observationAbout]] property identifies an entity, often a [[Place]], associated with an [[Observation]].

servingSize.name: servingSize
servingSize.description: The serving size, in terms of the number of volume or mass.

courseCode.name: courseCode
courseCode.description: The identifier for the [[Course]] used by the course [[provider]] (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

measurementQualifier.name: measurementQualifier
measurementQualifier.description: Provides additional qualification to an observation. For example, a GDP observation measures the Nominal value.

identifyingExam.name: identifyingExam
identifyingExam.description: A physical examination that can identify this sign.

creator.name: creator
creator.description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

checkinTime.name: checkinTime
checkinTime.description: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

cvdNumVent.name: cvdNumVent
cvdNumVent.description: numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

broadcaster.name: broadcaster
broadcaster.description: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

numberOfAirbags.name: numberOfAirbags
numberOfAirbags.description: The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

reviewedBy.name: reviewedBy
reviewedBy.description: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

associatedMediaReview.name: associatedMediaReview
associatedMediaReview.description: An associated [[MediaReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

suggestedAge.name: suggestedAge
suggestedAge.description: The age or age range for the intended audience or person, for example 3-12 months for infants, 1-5 years for toddlers.

measuredProperty.name: measuredProperty
measuredProperty.description: The measuredProperty of an [[Observation]], typically via its [[StatisticalVariable]]. There are various kinds of applicable [[Property]]: a schema.org property, a property from other RDF-compatible systems, e.g. W3C RDF Data Cube, Data Commons, Wikidata, or schema.org extensions such as [GS1's](https://www.gs1.org/voc/?show=properties).

publicationType.name: publicationType
publicationType.description: The type of the medical article, taken from the US NLM MeSH publication type catalog. See also [MeSH documentation](http://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/pubtypes.html).

includesObject.name: includesObject
includesObject.description: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

ownedThrough.name: ownedThrough
ownedThrough.description: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

returnPolicySeasonalOverride.name: returnPolicySeasonalOverride
returnPolicySeasonalOverride.description: Seasonal override of a return policy.

dateRead.name: dateRead
dateRead.description: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

titleEIDR.name: titleEIDR
titleEIDR.description: An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing at the most general/abstract level, a work of film or television. For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" has a titleEIDR of "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J". This title (or work) may have several variants, which EIDR calls "edits". See [[editEIDR]]. Since schema.org types like [[Movie]], [[TVEpisode]], [[TVSeason]], and [[TVSeries]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

itemCondition.name: itemCondition
itemCondition.description: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

bodyLocation.name: bodyLocation
bodyLocation.description: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

encoding.name: encoding
encoding.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

releasedEvent.name: releasedEvent
releasedEvent.description: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

accountablePerson.name: accountablePerson
accountablePerson.description: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

musicCompositionForm.name: musicCompositionForm
musicCompositionForm.description: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

educationalUse.name: educationalUse
educationalUse.description: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

subtitleLanguage.name: subtitleLanguage
subtitleLanguage.description: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in [IETF BCP 47 standard format](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

chemicalComposition.name: chemicalComposition
chemicalComposition.description: The chemical composition describes the identity and relative ratio of the chemical elements that make up the substance.

department.name: department
department.description: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

playMode.name: playMode
playMode.description: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player. The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

ticketedSeat.name: ticketedSeat
ticketedSeat.description: The seat associated with the ticket.

availableChannel.name: availableChannel
availableChannel.description: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

sizeGroup.name: sizeGroup
sizeGroup.description: The size group (also known as "size type") for a product's size. Size groups are common in the fashion industry to define size segments and suggested audiences for wearable products. Multiple values can be combined, for example "men's big and tall", "petite maternity" or "regular".

costCategory.name: costCategory
costCategory.description: The category of cost, such as wholesale, retail, reimbursement cap, etc.

cargoVolume.name: cargoVolume
cargoVolume.description:
The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.

Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet

Note: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

greaterOrEqual.name: greaterOrEqual
greaterOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

legalRepresentative.name: legalRepresentative
legalRepresentative.description: One or multiple persons who represent this organization legally such as CEO or sole administrator.

accountMinimumInflow.name: accountMinimumInflow
accountMinimumInflow.description: A minimum amount that has to be paid in every month.

bioChemSimilarity.name: bioChemSimilarity
bioChemSimilarity.description: A similar BioChemEntity, e.g., obtained by fingerprint similarity algorithms.

regionsAllowed.name: regionsAllowed
regionsAllowed.description: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in [ISO 3166 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166).

occupancy.name: occupancy
occupancy.description: The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person). Typical unit code(s): C62 for person.

physicalRequirement.name: physicalRequirement
physicalRequirement.description: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

isAcceptingNewPatients.name: isAcceptingNewPatients
isAcceptingNewPatients.description: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.

productionDate.name: productionDate
productionDate.description: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

fuelConsumption.name: fuelConsumption
fuelConsumption.description:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

sportsActivityLocation.name: sportsActivityLocation
sportsActivityLocation.description: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

activityFrequency.name: activityFrequency
activityFrequency.description: How often one should engage in the activity.

foundingLocation.name: foundingLocation
foundingLocation.description: The place where the Organization was founded.

schemaVersion.name: schemaVersion
schemaVersion.description: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. This property was created primarily to indicate the use of a specific schema.org release, e.g. ```10.0``` as a simple string, or more explicitly via URL, ```https://schema.org/docs/releases.html#v10.0```. There may be situations in which other schemas might usefully be referenced this way, e.g. ```http://dublincore.org/specifications/dublin-core/dces/1999-07-02/``` but this has not been carefully explored in the community.

companyRegistration.name: companyRegistration
companyRegistration.description: The official registration number of a business including the organization that issued it such as Company House or Chamber of Commerce.

businessFunction.name: businessFunction
businessFunction.description: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

minimumPaymentDue.name: minimumPaymentDue
minimumPaymentDue.description: The minimum payment required at this time.

durationOfWarranty.name: durationOfWarranty
durationOfWarranty.description: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

workFeatured.name: workFeatured
workFeatured.description: A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent. Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

codeSampleType.name: codeSampleType
codeSampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

acquiredFrom.name: acquiredFrom
acquiredFrom.description: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

dateVehicleFirstRegistered.name: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
dateVehicleFirstRegistered.description: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

hasMemberProgram.name: hasMemberProgram
hasMemberProgram.description: MemberProgram offered by an Organization, for example an eCommerce merchant or an airline.

member.name: member
member.description: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

catalogNumber.name: catalogNumber
catalogNumber.description: The catalog number for the release.

potentialAction.name: potentialAction
potentialAction.description: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

jurisdiction.name: jurisdiction
jurisdiction.description: Indicates a legal jurisdiction, e.g. of some legislation, or where some government service is based.

isUnlabelledFallback.name: isUnlabelledFallback
isUnlabelledFallback.description: This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] or [[ShippingRateSettings]] are intended to apply to all [[OfferShippingDetails]] published by the same merchant, when referenced by a [[shippingSettingsLink]] in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a transitTimeLabel (for [[DeliveryTimeSettings]]) or shippingLabel (for [[ShippingRateSettings]]), since this property is for use with unlabelled settings.

dateDeleted.name: dateDeleted
dateDeleted.description: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

adverseOutcome.name: adverseOutcome
adverseOutcome.description: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or otherwise life-threatening or requiring immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriousAdverseOutcome instead.

accessibilityHazard.name: accessibilityHazard
accessibilityHazard.description: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityHazard-vocabulary).

correction.name: correction
correction.description: Indicates a correction to a [[CreativeWork]], either via a [[CorrectionComment]], textually or in another document.

recipeYield.name: recipeYield
recipeYield.description: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).

appliesToPaymentMethod.name: appliesToPaymentMethod
appliesToPaymentMethod.description: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

pageStart.name: pageStart
pageStart.description: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

episodeNumber.name: episodeNumber
episodeNumber.description: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

fulfillmentType.name: fulfillmentType
fulfillmentType.description: Type of fulfillment applicable to the [[ShippingService]].

advanceBookingRequirement.name: advanceBookingRequirement
advanceBookingRequirement.description: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

doseValue.name: doseValue
doseValue.description: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

hasOccupation.name: hasOccupation
hasOccupation.description: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

differentialDiagnosis.name: differentialDiagnosis
differentialDiagnosis.description: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

printSection.name: printSection
printSection.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

doesNotShip.name: doesNotShip
doesNotShip.description: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

functionalClass.name: functionalClass
functionalClass.description: The degree of mobility the joint allows.

drugClass.name: drugClass
drugClass.description: The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

legislationCountersignedBy.name: legislationCountersignedBy
legislationCountersignedBy.description: The person or organization that countersigned the legislation. Depending on the legal context, a countersignature can indicate that the signed authority undertakes to assume responsibility for texts emanating from a person who is inviolable and irresponsible, (for example a King, Grand Duc or President), or that the authority is in charge of the implementation of the text.

geoDisjoint.name: geoDisjoint
geoDisjoint.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: "they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

menuAddOn.name: menuAddOn
menuAddOn.description: Additional menu item(s) such as a side dish of salad or side order of fries that can be added to this menu item. Additionally it can be a menu section containing allowed add-on menu items for this menu item.

collectionSize.name: collectionSize
collectionSize.description: The number of items in the [[Collection]].

arrivalAirport.name: arrivalAirport
arrivalAirport.description: The airport where the flight terminates.

buyer.name: buyer
buyer.description: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

proteinContent.name: proteinContent
proteinContent.description: The number of grams of protein.

travelBans.name: travelBans
travelBans.description: Information about travel bans, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

lifeEvent.name: lifeEvent
lifeEvent.description: A life event like baptism, communions, Bar Mitzvahs, Aqiqah, Namakarana, Miyamairi, burial, ....

rsvpResponse.name: rsvpResponse
rsvpResponse.description: The response (yes, no, maybe) to the RSVP.

documentation.name: documentation
documentation.description: Further documentation describing the Web API in more detail.

partOfSystem.name: partOfSystem
partOfSystem.description: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

actionApplication.name: actionApplication
actionApplication.description: An application that can complete the request.

isVariantOf.name: isVariantOf
isVariantOf.description: Indicates the kind of product that this is a variant of. In the case of [[ProductModel]], this is a pointer (from a ProductModel) to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive. In the case of a [[ProductGroup]], the group description also serves as a template, representing a set of Products that vary on explicitly defined, specific dimensions only (so it defines both a set of variants, as well as which values distinguish amongst those variants). When used with [[ProductGroup]], this property can apply to any [[Product]] included in the group.

bloodSupply.name: bloodSupply
bloodSupply.description: The blood vessel that carries blood from the heart to the muscle.

studyLocation.name: studyLocation
studyLocation.description: The location in which the study is taking/took place.

itemListElement.name: itemListElement
itemListElement.description:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements. Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

unitText.name: unitText
unitText.description: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

legislationCorrects.name: legislationCorrects
legislationCorrects.description: Another legislation in which this one introduces textual changes, like correction of spelling mistakes, with no legal impact (for modifications that have legal impact, use legislationAmends).

longitude.name: longitude
longitude.description: The longitude of a location. For example ```-122.08585``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

honorificSuffix.name: honorificSuffix
honorificSuffix.description: An honorific suffix following a Person's name such as M.D./PhD/MSCSW.

contactOption.name: contactOption
contactOption.description: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

inStoreReturnsOffered.name: inStoreReturnsOffered
inStoreReturnsOffered.description: Are in-store returns offered? (For more advanced return methods use the [[returnMethod]] property.)

minPrice.name: minPrice
minPrice.description: The lowest price if the price is a range.

geoIntersects.name: geoIntersects
geoIntersects.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

urlTemplate.name: urlTemplate
urlTemplate.description: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

healthPlanMarketingUrl.name: healthPlanMarketingUrl
healthPlanMarketingUrl.description: The URL that goes directly to the plan brochure for the specific standard plan or plan variation.

cvdNumVentUse.name: cvdNumVentUse
cvdNumVentUse.description: numventuse - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS IN USE: Total number of ventilators in use.

fuelType.name: fuelType
fuelType.description: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

availableService.name: availableService
availableService.description: A medical service available from this provider.

estimatedCost.name: estimatedCost
estimatedCost.description: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

speed.name: speed
speed.description:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by [[maxValue]]) should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.
* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.

subOrganization.name: subOrganization
subOrganization.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

temporal.name: temporal
temporal.description: The "temporal" property can be used in cases where more specific properties (e.g. [[temporalCoverage]], [[dateCreated]], [[dateModified]], [[datePublished]]) are not known to be appropriate.

announcementLocation.name: announcementLocation
announcementLocation.description: Indicates a specific [[CivicStructure]] or [[LocalBusiness]] associated with the SpecialAnnouncement. For example, a specific testing facility or business with special opening hours. For a larger geographic region like a quarantine of an entire region, use [[spatialCoverage]].

legalAddress.name: legalAddress
legalAddress.description: The legal address of an organization which acts as the officially registered address used for legal and tax purposes. The legal address can be different from the place of operations of a business and other addresses can be part of an organization.

targetProduct.name: targetProduct
targetProduct.description: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies. If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

studySubject.name: studySubject
studySubject.description: A subject of the study, i.e. one of the medical conditions, therapies, devices, drugs, etc. investigated by the study.

publishedBy.name: publishedBy
publishedBy.description: An agent associated with the publication event.

isSimilarTo.name: isSimilarTo
isSimilarTo.description: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

stageAsNumber.name: stageAsNumber
stageAsNumber.description: The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

orderValue.name: orderValue
orderValue.description: Minimum and maximum order value for which these shipping conditions are valid.

energyEfficiencyScaleMax.name: energyEfficiencyScaleMax
energyEfficiencyScaleMax.description: Specifies the most energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

byMonthDay.name: byMonthDay
byMonthDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the month on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-31.

speakable.name: speakable
speakable.description: Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech. The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values: 1.) *id-value* URL references - uses *id-value* of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of *speakable* has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned. 2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, e.g. via class attribute. Use the [[cssSelector]] property. 3.) XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the [[xpath]] property. For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this we define a supporting type, [[SpeakableSpecification]] which is defined to be a possible value of the *speakable* property.

relatedStructure.name: relatedStructure
relatedStructure.description: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

nextItem.name: nextItem
nextItem.description: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

requiresSubscription.name: requiresSubscription
requiresSubscription.description: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription (either paid or free). Allowed values are ```true``` or ```false``` (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

dropoffLocation.name: dropoffLocation
dropoffLocation.description: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

executableLibraryName.name: executableLibraryName
executableLibraryName.description: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

gracePeriod.name: gracePeriod
gracePeriod.description: The period of time after any due date that the borrower has to fulfil its obligations before a default (failure to pay) is deemed to have occurred.

reservationStatus.name: reservationStatus
reservationStatus.description: The current status of the reservation.

instrument.name: instrument
instrument.description: The object that helped the agent perform the action. E.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.

checkoutTime.name: checkoutTime
checkoutTime.description: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

expires.name: expires
expires.description: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a [[VideoObject]] or [[NewsArticle]] whose availability or relevance is time-limited, a [[ClaimReview]] fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date, or a [[Certification]] the validity has expired.

interestRate.name: interestRate
interestRate.description: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

physiologicalBenefits.name: physiologicalBenefits
physiologicalBenefits.description: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

relatedCondition.name: relatedCondition
relatedCondition.description: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

variableMeasured.name: variableMeasured
variableMeasured.description: The variableMeasured property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue, or more explicitly as a [[StatisticalVariable]].

knows.name: knows
knows.description: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

numberOfEpisodes.name: numberOfEpisodes
numberOfEpisodes.description: The number of episodes in this season or series.

programType.name: programType
programType.description: The type of educational or occupational program. For example, classroom, internship, alternance, etc.

energyEfficiencyScaleMin.name: energyEfficiencyScaleMin
energyEfficiencyScaleMin.description: Specifies the least energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

engineType.name: engineType
engineType.description: The type of engine or engines powering the vehicle.

merchantReturnLink.name: merchantReturnLink
merchantReturnLink.description: Specifies a Web page or service by URL, for product returns.

applicationCategory.name: applicationCategory
applicationCategory.description: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

hasDeliveryMethod.name: hasDeliveryMethod
hasDeliveryMethod.description: Method used for delivery or shipping.

replacee.name: replacee
replacee.description: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.

aggregateElement.name: aggregateElement
aggregateElement.description: Indicates a prototype of the elements in the list that is used to hold aggregate information (ratings, offers, etc.).

industry.name: industry
industry.description: The industry associated with the job position.

paymentMethod.name: paymentMethod
paymentMethod.description: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

diet.name: diet
diet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

endorsee.name: endorsee
endorsee.description: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

copyrightNotice.name: copyrightNotice
copyrightNotice.description: Text of a notice appropriate for describing the copyright aspects of this Creative Work, ideally indicating the owner of the copyright for the Work.

boardingGroup.name: boardingGroup
boardingGroup.description: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

exchangeRateSpread.name: exchangeRateSpread
exchangeRateSpread.description: The difference between the price at which a broker or other intermediary buys and sells foreign currency.

isEncodedByBioChemEntity.name: isEncodedByBioChemEntity
isEncodedByBioChemEntity.description: Another BioChemEntity encoding by this one.

prescriptionStatus.name: prescriptionStatus
prescriptionStatus.description: Indicates the status of drug prescription, e.g. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

starRating.name: starRating
starRating.description: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

newsUpdatesAndGuidelines.name: newsUpdatesAndGuidelines
newsUpdatesAndGuidelines.description: Indicates a page with news updates and guidelines. This could often be (but is not required to be) the main page containing [[SpecialAnnouncement]] markup on a site.

broadcastAffiliateOf.name: broadcastAffiliateOf
broadcastAffiliateOf.description: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

infectiousAgent.name: infectiousAgent
infectiousAgent.description: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.

netWorth.name: netWorth
netWorth.description: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting the total value of liabilities from the total value of assets.

availableIn.name: availableIn
availableIn.description: The location in which the strength is available.

cvdFacilityCounty.name: cvdFacilityCounty
cvdFacilityCounty.description: Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityId]] to identify the facility. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

hiringOrganization.name: hiringOrganization
hiringOrganization.description: Organization or Person offering the job position.

offerCount.name: offerCount
offerCount.description: The number of offers for the product.

jobLocationType.name: jobLocationType
jobLocationType.description: A description of the job location (e.g. TELECOMMUTE for telecommute jobs).

recipeCuisine.name: recipeCuisine
recipeCuisine.description: The cuisine of the recipe (for example, French or Ethiopian).

estimatesRiskOf.name: estimatesRiskOf
estimatesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

recognizingAuthority.name: recognizingAuthority
recognizingAuthority.description: If applicable, the organization that officially recognizes this entity as part of its endorsed system of medicine.

discountCode.name: discountCode
discountCode.description: Code used to redeem a discount.

hasSponsorshipOffer.name: hasSponsorshipOffer
hasSponsorshipOffer.description: An offer to sponsor the event, for example, Sponsorship Prospectus, Sponsorship Opportunities, or Sponsor Packages.

mpn.name: mpn
mpn.description: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

coverageEndTime.name: coverageEndTime
coverageEndTime.description: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

warrantyScope.name: warrantyScope
warrantyScope.description: The scope of the warranty promise.

drugUnit.name: drugUnit
drugUnit.description: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

greater.name: greater
greater.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

risks.name: risks
risks.description: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.

incentiveType.name: incentiveType
incentiveType.description: The type of incentive offered (tax credit/rebate, tax deduction, tax waiver, subsidies, etc.).

arrivalBusStop.name: arrivalBusStop
arrivalBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

programPrerequisites.name: programPrerequisites
programPrerequisites.description: Prerequisites for enrolling in the program.

shippingOrigin.name: shippingOrigin
shippingOrigin.description: Indicates the origin of a shipment, i.e. where it should be coming from.

workLocation.name: workLocation
workLocation.description: A contact location for a person's place of work.

priceRange.name: priceRange
priceRange.description: The price range of the business, for example ```$$$```.

predecessorOf.name: predecessorOf
predecessorOf.description: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

contactType.name: contactType
contactType.description: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

educationRequirements.name: educationRequirements
educationRequirements.description: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

competitor.name: competitor
competitor.description: A competitor in a sports event.

installUrl.name: installUrl
installUrl.description: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

eligibleRegion.name: eligibleRegion
eligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

ratingCount.name: ratingCount
ratingCount.description: The count of total number of ratings.

gameItem.name: gameItem
gameItem.description: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

creditedTo.name: creditedTo
creditedTo.description: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

legislationResponsible.name: legislationResponsible
legislationResponsible.description: An individual or organization that has some kind of responsibility for the legislation. Typically the ministry who is/was in charge of elaborating the legislation, or the adressee for potential questions about the legislation once it is published.

ratingValue.name: ratingValue
ratingValue.description:
The rating for the content.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

stepValue.name: stepValue
stepValue.description: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

numItems.name: numItems
numItems.description: Limits the number of items being shipped for which these conditions apply.

previousItem.name: previousItem
previousItem.description: A link to the ListItem that precedes the current one.

numberOfLoanPayments.name: numberOfLoanPayments
numberOfLoanPayments.description: The number of payments contractually required at origination to repay the loan. For monthly paying loans this is the number of months from the contractual first payment date to the maturity date.

frequency.name: frequency
frequency.description: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

partySize.name: partySize
partySize.description: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

includedRiskFactor.name: includedRiskFactor
includedRiskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable risk factor included in the calculation, e.g. age, coexisting condition.

musicReleaseFormat.name: musicReleaseFormat
musicReleaseFormat.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

restPeriods.name: restPeriods
restPeriods.description: How often one should break from the activity.

sdDatePublished.name: sdDatePublished
sdDatePublished.description: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside [[sdPublisher]].

cvdNumICUBedsOcc.name: cvdNumICUBedsOcc
cvdNumICUBedsOcc.description: numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

petsAllowed.name: petsAllowed
petsAllowed.description: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

doseUnit.name: doseUnit
doseUnit.description: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

engineDisplacement.name: engineDisplacement
engineDisplacement.description:
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement. 

Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches
* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

teaches.name: teaches
teaches.description: The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

deliveryTime.name: deliveryTime
deliveryTime.description: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

carbohydrateContent.name: carbohydrateContent
carbohydrateContent.description: The number of grams of carbohydrates.

hasMenu.name: hasMenu
hasMenu.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

healthPlanId.name: healthPlanId
healthPlanId.description: The 14-character, HIOS-generated Plan ID number. (Plan IDs must be unique, even across different markets.)

reviewRating.name: reviewRating
reviewRating.description: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The ```reviewRating``` applies to rating given by the review. The [[aggregateRating]] property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

sportsTeam.name: sportsTeam
sportsTeam.description: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

screenCount.name: screenCount
screenCount.description: The number of screens in the movie theater.

alcoholWarning.name: alcoholWarning
alcoholWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

partOfSeries.name: partOfSeries
partOfSeries.description: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

businessDays.name: businessDays
businessDays.description: Days of the week when the merchant typically operates, indicated via opening hours markup.

dataset.name: dataset
dataset.description: A dataset contained in this catalog.

alumniOf.name: alumniOf
alumniOf.description: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

numberOfItems.name: numberOfItems
numberOfItems.description: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

publishingPrinciples.name: publishingPrinciples
publishingPrinciples.description: The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual, e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]]. While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a [[funder]]) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

hasStore.name: hasStore
hasStore.description: An eCommerce store part of an online marketplace.

productionCompany.name: productionCompany
productionCompany.description: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

trackingUrl.name: trackingUrl
trackingUrl.description: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

valueMaxLength.name: valueMaxLength
valueMaxLength.description: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

nerveMotor.name: nerveMotor
nerveMotor.description: The neurological pathway extension that involves muscle control.

hasHealthAspect.name: hasHealthAspect
hasHealthAspect.description: Indicates the aspect or aspects specifically addressed in some [[HealthTopicContent]]. For example, that the content is an overview, or that it talks about treatment, self-care, treatments or their side-effects.

editor.name: editor
editor.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

exceptDate.name: exceptDate
exceptDate.description: Defines a [[Date]] or [[DateTime]] during which a scheduled [[Event]] will not take place. The property allows exceptions to a [[Schedule]] to be specified. If an exception is specified as a [[DateTime]] then only the event that would have started at that specific date and time should be excluded from the schedule. If an exception is specified as a [[Date]] then any event that is scheduled for that 24 hour period should be excluded from the schedule. This allows a whole day to be excluded from the schedule without having to itemise every scheduled event.

interactionType.name: interactionType
interactionType.description: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use [[LikeAction]]. For down votes use [[DislikeAction]]. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

spatialCoverage.name: spatialCoverage
spatialCoverage.description: The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

suggestedMeasurement.name: suggestedMeasurement
suggestedMeasurement.description: A suggested range of body measurements for the intended audience or person, for example inseam between 32 and 34 inches or height between 170 and 190 cm. Typically found on a size chart for wearable products.

entertainmentBusiness.name: entertainmentBusiness
entertainmentBusiness.description: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

award.name: award
award.description: An award won by or for this item.

inChIKey.name: inChIKey
inChIKey.description: InChIKey is a hashed version of the full InChI (using the SHA-256 algorithm).

targetCollection.name: targetCollection
targetCollection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

ownershipFundingInfo.name: ownershipFundingInfo
ownershipFundingInfo.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence. Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

doseSchedule.name: doseSchedule
doseSchedule.description: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

mealService.name: mealService
mealService.description: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

purchasePriceLimit.name: purchasePriceLimit
purchasePriceLimit.description: Optional. The maximum price the item can have and still qualify for this offer.

usageInfo.name: usageInfo
usageInfo.description: The schema.org [[usageInfo]] property indicates further information about a [[CreativeWork]]. This property is applicable both to works that are freely available and to those that require payment or other transactions. It can reference additional information, e.g. community expectations on preferred linking and citation conventions, as well as purchasing details. For something that can be commercially licensed, usageInfo can provide detailed, resource-specific information about licensing options. This property can be used alongside the license property which indicates license(s) applicable to some piece of content. The usageInfo property can provide information about other licensing options, e.g. acquiring commercial usage rights for an image that is also available under non-commercial creative commons licenses.

jobTitle.name: jobTitle
jobTitle.description: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

infectiousAgentClass.name: infectiousAgentClass
infectiousAgentClass.description: The class of infectious agent (bacteria, prion, etc.) that causes the disease.

replyToUrl.name: replyToUrl
replyToUrl.description: The URL at which a reply may be posted to the specified UserComment.

floorLevel.name: floorLevel
floorLevel.description: The floor level for an [[Accommodation]] in a multi-storey building. Since counting systems [vary internationally](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storey#Consecutive_number_floor_designations), the local system should be used where possible.

sportsEvent.name: sportsEvent
sportsEvent.description: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

taxID.name: taxID
taxID.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

followee.name: followee
followee.description: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

dateSent.name: dateSent
dateSent.description: The date/time at which the message was sent.

overdosage.name: overdosage
overdosage.description: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount.name: monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount
monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount.description: The minimum payment is the lowest amount of money that one is required to pay on a credit card statement each month.

isAccessibleForFree.name: isAccessibleForFree
isAccessibleForFree.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

about.name: about
about.description: The subject matter of an object.

endTime.name: endTime
endTime.description: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

numConstraints.name: numConstraints
numConstraints.description: Indicates the number of constraints property values defined for a particular [[ConstraintNode]] such as [[StatisticalVariable]]. This helps applications understand if they have access to a sufficiently complete description of a [[StatisticalVariable]] or other construct that is defined using properties on template-style nodes.

activeIngredient.name: activeIngredient
activeIngredient.description: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

hostingOrganization.name: hostingOrganization
hostingOrganization.description: The Organization (airline, travelers' club, retailer, etc.) the membership is made with or which offers the MemberProgram.

clinicalPharmacology.name: clinicalPharmacology
clinicalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

numberOfBedrooms.name: numberOfBedrooms
numberOfBedrooms.description: The total integer number of bedrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], [[ApartmentComplex]] or [[FloorPlan]].

discussionUrl.name: discussionUrl
discussionUrl.description: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

numberOfPlayers.name: numberOfPlayers
numberOfPlayers.description: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

inSupportOf.name: inSupportOf
inSupportOf.description: Qualification, candidature, degree, application that Thesis supports.

encodesCreativeWork.name: encodesCreativeWork
encodesCreativeWork.description: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

model.name: model
model.description: The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

beforeMedia.name: beforeMedia
beforeMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

partOfEpisode.name: partOfEpisode
partOfEpisode.description: The episode to which this clip belongs.

athlete.name: athlete
athlete.description: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.

pagination.name: pagination
pagination.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

hasCategoryCode.name: hasCategoryCode
hasCategoryCode.description: A Category code contained in this code set.

biologicalRole.name: biologicalRole
biologicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a biological context.

duplicateTherapy.name: duplicateTherapy
duplicateTherapy.description: A therapy that duplicates or overlaps this one.

screenshot.name: screenshot
screenshot.description: A link to a screenshot image of the app.

certificationIdentification.name: certificationIdentification
certificationIdentification.description: Identifier of a certification instance (as registered with an independent certification body). Typically this identifier can be used to consult and verify the certification instance. See also [gs1:certificationIdentification](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationIdentification).

subReservation.name: subReservation
subReservation.description: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

familyName.name: familyName
familyName.description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

additionalVariable.name: additionalVariable
additionalVariable.description: Any additional component of the exercise prescription that may need to be articulated to the patient. This may include the order of exercises, the number of repetitions of movement, quantitative distance, progressions over time, etc.

supplyTo.name: supplyTo
supplyTo.description: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

billingIncrement.name: billingIncrement
billingIncrement.description: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

diversityPolicy.name: diversityPolicy
diversityPolicy.description: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsrooms diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

countryOfOrigin.name: countryOfOrigin
countryOfOrigin.description: The country of origin of something, including products as well as creative works such as movie and TV content. In the case of TV and movie, this would be the country of the principle offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie. For other kinds of [[CreativeWork]] it is difficult to provide fully general guidance, and properties such as [[contentLocation]] and [[locationCreated]] may be more applicable. In the case of products, the country of origin of the product. The exact interpretation of this may vary by context and product type, and cannot be fully enumerated here.

articleBody.name: articleBody
articleBody.description: The actual body of the article.

availabilityStarts.name: availabilityStarts
availabilityStarts.description: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

deliveryStatus.name: deliveryStatus
deliveryStatus.description: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

hasCredential.name: hasCredential
hasCredential.description: A credential awarded to the Person or Organization.

paymentMethodId.name: paymentMethodId
paymentMethodId.description: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

artEdition.name: artEdition
artEdition.description: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

causeOf.name: causeOf
causeOf.description: The condition, complication, symptom, sign, etc. caused.

isAvailableGenerically.name: isAvailableGenerically
isAvailableGenerically.description: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).

parentItem.name: parentItem
parentItem.description: The parent of a question, answer or item in general. Typically used for Q/A discussion threads e.g. a chain of comments with the first comment being an [[Article]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. See also [[comment]] which points from something to a comment about it.

encodingType.name: encodingType
encodingType.description: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

sponsor.name: sponsor
sponsor.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

downloadUrl.name: downloadUrl
downloadUrl.description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

valueMinLength.name: valueMinLength
valueMinLength.description: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

coach.name: coach
coach.description: A person that acts in a coaching role for a sports team.

performerIn.name: performerIn
performerIn.description: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

isConsumableFor.name: isConsumableFor
isConsumableFor.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity.name: maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity
maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity.description: The maximum physical attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OfflineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the offline aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

agentInteractionStatistic.name: agentInteractionStatistic
agentInteractionStatistic.description: The number of completed interactions for this entity, in a particular role (the 'agent'), in a particular action (indicated in the statistic), and in a particular context (i.e. interactionService).

masthead.name: masthead
masthead.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a link to the masthead page or a page listing top editorial management.

bccRecipient.name: bccRecipient
bccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

dataFeedElement.name: dataFeedElement
dataFeedElement.description: An item within a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

billingStart.name: billingStart
billingStart.description: Specifies after how much time this price (or price component) becomes valid and billing starts. Can be used, for example, to model a price increase after the first year of a subscription. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

primaryPrevention.name: primaryPrevention
primaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

serviceOperator.name: serviceOperator
serviceOperator.description: The operating organization, if different from the provider. This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

includedComposition.name: includedComposition
includedComposition.description: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

recipeCategory.name: recipeCategory
recipeCategory.description: The category of the recipefor example, appetizer, entree, etc.

geoWithin.name: geoWithin
geoWithin.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

givenName.name: givenName
givenName.description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

branchCode.name: branchCode
branchCode.description: A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.\n\nFor example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

borrower.name: borrower
borrower.description: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

subTest.name: subTest
subTest.description: A component test of the panel.

musicalKey.name: musicalKey
musicalKey.description: The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

error.name: error
error.description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure. Consider using the Error type.

startOffset.name: startOffset
startOffset.description: The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

cvdFacilityId.name: cvdFacilityId
cvdFacilityId.description: Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityCounty]] to indicate the county. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

partOfTrip.name: partOfTrip
partOfTrip.description: Identifies that this [[Trip]] is a subTrip of another Trip. For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

geoCoveredBy.name: geoCoveredBy
geoCoveredBy.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

abridged.name: abridged
abridged.description: Indicates whether the book is an abridged edition.

lastReviewed.name: lastReviewed
lastReviewed.description: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

cvdNumBeds.name: cvdNumBeds
cvdNumBeds.description: numbeds - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BEDS: Inpatient beds, including all staffed, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients.

worksFor.name: worksFor
worksFor.description: Organizations that the person works for.

specialty.name: specialty
specialty.description: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

interactivityType.name: interactivityType
interactivityType.description: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

includedInDataCatalog.name: includedInDataCatalog
includedInDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

numberedPosition.name: numberedPosition
numberedPosition.description: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

maximumAttendeeCapacity.name: maximumAttendeeCapacity
maximumAttendeeCapacity.description: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

guideline.name: guideline
guideline.description: A medical guideline related to this entity.

associatedPathophysiology.name: associatedPathophysiology
associatedPathophysiology.description: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

lesser.name: lesser
lesser.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

returnPolicyCountry.name: returnPolicyCountry
returnPolicyCountry.description: The country where the product has to be sent to for returns, for example "Ireland" using the [[name]] property of [[Country]]. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1). Note that this can be different from the country where the product was originally shipped from or sent to.

translator.name: translator
translator.description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

eligibleTransactionVolume.name: eligibleTransactionVolume
eligibleTransactionVolume.description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

healthPlanDrugTier.name: healthPlanDrugTier
healthPlanDrugTier.description: The tier(s) of drugs offered by this formulary or insurance plan.

creditText.name: creditText
creditText.description: Text that can be used to credit person(s) and/or organization(s) associated with a published Creative Work.

vehicleInteriorColor.name: vehicleInteriorColor
vehicleInteriorColor.description: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

taxonomicRange.name: taxonomicRange
taxonomicRange.description: The taxonomic grouping of the organism that expresses, encodes, or in some way related to the BioChemEntity.

location.name: location
location.description: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

legislationAmends.name: legislationAmends
legislationAmends.description: Another legislation that this legislation amends, introducing legal changes.

inCodeSet.name: inCodeSet
inCodeSet.description: A [[CategoryCodeSet]] that contains this category code.

timeOfDay.name: timeOfDay
timeOfDay.description: The time of day the program normally runs. For example, "evenings".

messageAttachment.name: messageAttachment
messageAttachment.description: A CreativeWork attached to the message.

offersPrescriptionByMail.name: offersPrescriptionByMail
offersPrescriptionByMail.description: Whether prescriptions can be delivered by mail.

letterer.name: letterer
letterer.description: The individual who adds lettering, including speech balloons and sound effects, to artwork.

availableTest.name: availableTest
availableTest.description: A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.

seeks.name: seeks
seeks.description: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

legislationDate.name: legislationDate
legislationDate.description: The date of adoption or signature of the legislation. This is the date at which the text is officially aknowledged to be a legislation, even though it might not even be published or in force.

serviceLocation.name: serviceLocation
serviceLocation.description: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

applicationSubCategory.name: applicationSubCategory
applicationSubCategory.description: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

numberOfPages.name: numberOfPages
numberOfPages.description: The number of pages in the book.

mapType.name: mapType
mapType.description: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

ratingExplanation.name: ratingExplanation
ratingExplanation.description: A short explanation (e.g. one to two sentences) providing background context and other information that led to the conclusion expressed in the rating. This is particularly applicable to ratings associated with "fact check" markup using [[ClaimReview]].

contributor.name: contributor
contributor.description: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

paymentDueDate.name: paymentDueDate
paymentDueDate.description: The date that payment is due.

translationOfWork.name: translationOfWork
translationOfWork.description: The work that this work has been translated from. E.g.  is a translationOf On the Origin of Species.

winner.name: winner
winner.description: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

utterances.name: utterances
utterances.description: Text of an utterances (spoken words, lyrics etc.) that occurs at a certain section of a media object, represented as a [[HyperTocEntry]].

loanType.name: loanType
loanType.description: The type of a loan or credit.

passengerSequenceNumber.name: passengerSequenceNumber
passengerSequenceNumber.description: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

makesOffer.name: makesOffer
makesOffer.description: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

applicationSuite.name: applicationSuite
applicationSuite.description: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

alternativeOf.name: alternativeOf
alternativeOf.description: Another gene which is a variation of this one.

enginePower.name: enginePower
enginePower.description:
The power of the vehicle's engine. Typical unit code(s): KWT for kilowatt, BHP for brake horsepower, N12 for metric horsepower (PS, with 1 PS = 735,49875 W)

* Note 1: There are many different ways of measuring an engine's power. For an overview, see [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine\_power\_test\_codes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine_power_test_codes).
* Note 2: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 3: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

verificationFactCheckingPolicy.name: verificationFactCheckingPolicy
verificationFactCheckingPolicy.description: Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other fact-checking [[Organization]].

productGroupID.name: productGroupID
productGroupID.description: Indicates a textual identifier for a ProductGroup.

legislationApplies.name: legislationApplies
legislationApplies.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of a legislation) somehow transfers another legislation in a different legislative context. This is an informative link, and it has no legal value. For legally-binding links of transposition, use the legislationTransposes property. For example an informative consolidated law of a European Union's member state "applies" the consolidated version of the European Directive implemented in it.

observationPeriod.name: observationPeriod
observationPeriod.description: The length of time an Observation took place over. The format follows `P[0-9]*[Y|M|D|h|m|s]`. For example, P1Y is Period 1 Year, P3M is Period 3 Months, P3h is Period 3 hours.

inPlaylist.name: inPlaylist
inPlaylist.description: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

vatID.name: vatID
vatID.description: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

valueRequired.name: valueRequired
valueRequired.description: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action. Default is false.

associatedMedia.name: associatedMedia
associatedMedia.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

participant.name: participant
participant.description: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. E.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

discountCurrency.name: discountCurrency
discountCurrency.description: The currency of the discount.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

maximumIntake.name: maximumIntake
maximumIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

datePosted.name: datePosted
datePosted.description: Publication date of an online listing.

originatesFrom.name: originatesFrom
originatesFrom.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

permissions.name: permissions
permissions.description: Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

molecularWeight.name: molecularWeight
molecularWeight.description: This is the molecular weight of the entity being described, not of the parent. Units should be included in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '12 amu' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

nonProprietaryName.name: nonProprietaryName
nonProprietaryName.description: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

pattern.name: pattern
pattern.description: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.

asin.name: asin
asin.description: An Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN) is a 10-character alphanumeric unique identifier assigned by Amazon.com and its partners for product identification within the Amazon organization (summary from [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Standard_Identification_Number)'s article). Note also that this is a definition for how to include ASINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of ASINs in general - see documentation from Amazon for authoritative details.
