ASINs are most commonly encoded as text strings, but the [asin] property supports URL/URI as potential values too.

gamePlatform.name: gamePlatform
gamePlatform.description: The electronic systems used to play video games.

directApply.name: directApply
directApply.description: Indicates whether an [[url]] that is associated with a [[JobPosting]] enables direct application for the job, via the posting website. A job posting is considered to have directApply of [[True]] if an application process for the specified job can be directly initiated via the url(s) given (noting that e.g. multiple internet domains might nevertheless be involved at an implementation level). A value of [[False]] is appropriate if there is no clear path to applying directly online for the specified job, navigating directly from the JobPosting url(s) supplied.

educationalAlignment.name: educationalAlignment
educationalAlignment.description: An alignment to an established educational framework. This property should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource [[teaches]] or [[assesses]] a competency.

usesHealthPlanIdStandard.name: usesHealthPlanIdStandard
usesHealthPlanIdStandard.description: The standard for interpreting the Plan ID. The preferred is "HIOS". See the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services for more details.

serialNumber.name: serialNumber
serialNumber.description: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

previousStartDate.name: previousStartDate
previousStartDate.description: Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

credentialCategory.name: credentialCategory
credentialCategory.description: The category or type of credential being described, for example "degree, certificate, badge, or more specific term.

gameLocation.name: gameLocation
gameLocation.description: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

incentiveStatus.name: incentiveStatus
incentiveStatus.description: The status of the incentive (active, on hold, retired, etc.).

hasCourse.name: hasCourse
hasCourse.description: A course or class that is one of the learning opportunities that constitute an educational / occupational program. No information is implied about whether the course is mandatory or optional; no guarantee is implied about whether the course will be available to everyone on the program.

weightPercentage.name: weightPercentage
weightPercentage.description: Value in the range [0.0 ; 1.0] representing the fraction of the weight that is used to compute the shipping price.

accessibilityAPI.name: accessibilityAPI
accessibilityAPI.description: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityAPI-vocabulary).

duns.name: duns
duns.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

geoTouches.name: geoTouches
geoTouches.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: "they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

box.name: box
box.description: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

worstRating.name: worstRating
worstRating.description: The lowest value allowed in this rating system.

director.name: director
director.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

characterName.name: characterName
characterName.description: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

chemicalRole.name: chemicalRole
chemicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a chemical context.

diagram.name: diagram
diagram.description: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

providesBroadcastService.name: providesBroadcastService
providesBroadcastService.description: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

artMedium.name: artMedium
artMedium.description: The material used. (E.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

termCode.name: termCode
termCode.description: A code that identifies this [[DefinedTerm]] within a [[DefinedTermSet]].

fuelEfficiency.name: fuelEfficiency
fuelEfficiency.description:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

loser.name: loser
loser.description: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

hasShippingService.name: hasShippingService
hasShippingService.description: Specification of a shipping service offered by the organization.

variantCover.name: variantCover
variantCover.description: A description of the variant cover for the issue, if the issue is a variant printing. For example, "Bryan Hitch Variant Cover" or "2nd Printing Variant".

image.name: image
image.description: An image of the item. This can be a [[URL]] or a fully described [[ImageObject]].

confirmationNumber.name: confirmationNumber
confirmationNumber.description: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

totalTime.name: totalTime
totalTime.description: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

homeLocation.name: homeLocation
homeLocation.description: A contact location for a person's residence.

offeredBy.name: offeredBy
offeredBy.description: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

billingAddress.name: billingAddress
billingAddress.description: The billing address for the order.

accessibilitySummary.name: accessibilitySummary
accessibilitySummary.description: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed".

embeddedTextCaption.name: embeddedTextCaption
embeddedTextCaption.description: Represents textual captioning from a [[MediaObject]], e.g. text of a 'meme'.

exampleOfWork.name: exampleOfWork
exampleOfWork.description: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

publication.name: publication
publication.description: A publication event associated with the item.

reviewBody.name: reviewBody
reviewBody.description: The actual body of the review.

fundedItem.name: fundedItem
fundedItem.description: Indicates something directly or indirectly funded or sponsored through a [[Grant]]. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

vehicleModelDate.name: vehicleModelDate
vehicleModelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

eligibleQuantity.name: eligibleQuantity
eligibleQuantity.description: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

repeatCount.name: repeatCount
repeatCount.description: Defines the number of times a recurring [[Event]] will take place.

pregnancyWarning.name: pregnancyWarning
pregnancyWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

tripOrigin.name: tripOrigin
tripOrigin.description: The location of origin of the trip, prior to any destination(s).

performTime.name: performTime
performTime.description: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

hasPOS.name: hasPOS
hasPOS.description: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

bitrate.name: bitrate
bitrate.description: The bitrate of the media object.

busName.name: busName
busName.description: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

softwareAddOn.name: softwareAddOn
softwareAddOn.description: Additional content for a software application.

isAccessoryOrSparePartFor.name: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
isAccessoryOrSparePartFor.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

foodWarning.name: foodWarning
foodWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of specific foods while taking this drug.

paymentAccepted.name: paymentAccepted
paymentAccepted.description: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

driveWheelConfiguration.name: driveWheelConfiguration
driveWheelConfiguration.description: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

seatNumber.name: seatNumber
seatNumber.description: The location of the reserved seat (e.g., 27).

departureBusStop.name: departureBusStop
departureBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

medicineSystem.name: medicineSystem
medicineSystem.description: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

disambiguatingDescription.name: disambiguatingDescription
disambiguatingDescription.description: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

responsibilities.name: responsibilities
responsibilities.description: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

isLocatedInSubcellularLocation.name: isLocatedInSubcellularLocation
isLocatedInSubcellularLocation.description: Subcellular location where this BioChemEntity is located; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

countriesNotSupported.name: countriesNotSupported
countriesNotSupported.description: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

position.name: position
position.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

relatedLink.name: relatedLink
relatedLink.description: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

validThrough.name: validThrough
validThrough.description: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

tissueSample.name: tissueSample
tissueSample.description: The type of tissue sample required for the test.

hasGS1DigitalLink.name: hasGS1DigitalLink
hasGS1DigitalLink.description: The GS1 digital link associated with the object. This URL should conform to the particular requirements of digital links. The link should only contain the Application Identifiers (AIs) that are relevant for the entity being annotated, for instance a [[Product]] or an [[Organization]], and for the correct granularity. In particular, for products:A Digital Link that contains a serial number (AI 21) should only be present on instances of [[IndividualProduct]]A Digital Link that contains a lot number (AI 10) should be annotated as [[SomeProduct]] if only products from that lot are sold, or [[IndividualProduct]] if there is only a specific product.A Digital Link that contains a global model number (AI 8013) should be attached to a [[Product]] or a [[ProductModel]]. Other item types should be adapted similarly.

conditionsOfAccess.name: conditionsOfAccess
conditionsOfAccess.description: Conditions that affect the availability of, or method(s) of access to, an item. Typically used for real world items such as an [[ArchiveComponent]] held by an [[ArchiveOrganization]]. This property is not suitable for use as a general Web access control mechanism. It is expressed only in natural language.\n\nFor example "Available by appointment from the Reading Room" or "Accessible only from logged-in accounts ".

mainEntity.name: mainEntity
mainEntity.description: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

copyrightYear.name: copyrightYear
copyrightYear.description: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

acrissCode.name: acrissCode
acrissCode.description: The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies, for classifying vehicles. ACRISS stands for Association of Car Rental Industry Systems and Standards.

additionalName.name: additionalName
additionalName.description: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

text.name: text
text.description: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

contentUrl.name: contentUrl
contentUrl.description: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

seatRow.name: seatRow
seatRow.description: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

cashBack.name: cashBack
cashBack.description: A cardholder benefit that pays the cardholder a small percentage of their net expenditures.

reservedTicket.name: reservedTicket
reservedTicket.description: A ticket associated with the reservation.

tickerSymbol.name: tickerSymbol
tickerSymbol.description: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO 15022.

defaultValue.name: defaultValue
defaultValue.description: The default value of the input. For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

childTaxon.name: childTaxon
childTaxon.description: Closest child taxa of the taxon in question.

releaseDate.name: releaseDate
releaseDate.description: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

preparation.name: preparation
preparation.description: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

interpretedAsClaim.name: interpretedAsClaim
interpretedAsClaim.description: Used to indicate a specific claim contained, implied, translated or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. The interpreting party can be indicated using [[claimInterpreter]].

procedure.name: procedure
procedure.description: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

diagnosis.name: diagnosis
diagnosis.description: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

callSign.name: callSign
callSign.description: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

cookTime.name: cookTime
cookTime.description: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

hasOfferCatalog.name: hasOfferCatalog
hasOfferCatalog.description: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

isPartOf.name: isPartOf
isPartOf.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

legislationChanges.name: legislationChanges
legislationChanges.description: Another legislation that this legislation changes. This encompasses the notions of amendment, replacement, correction, repeal, or other types of change. This may be a direct change (textual or non-textual amendment) or a consequential or indirect change. The property is to be used to express the existence of a change relationship between two acts rather than the existence of a consolidated version of the text that shows the result of the change. For consolidation relationships, use the legislationConsolidates property.

deathPlace.name: deathPlace
deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

claimInterpreter.name: claimInterpreter
claimInterpreter.description: For a [[Claim]] interpreted from [[MediaObject]] content, the [[interpretedAsClaim]] property can be used to indicate a claim contained, implied or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]].

landlord.name: landlord
landlord.description: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

antagonist.name: antagonist
antagonist.description: The muscle whose action counteracts the specified muscle.

nonprofitStatus.name: nonprofitStatus
nonprofitStatus.description: nonprofitStatus indicates the legal status of a non-profit organization in its primary place of business.

transmissionMethod.name: transmissionMethod
transmissionMethod.description: How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

itemListOrder.name: itemListOrder
itemListOrder.description: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

shippingRate.name: shippingRate
shippingRate.description: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

termDuration.name: termDuration
termDuration.description: The amount of time in a term as defined by the institution. A term is a length of time where students take one or more classes. Semesters and quarters are common units for term.

linkRelationship.name: linkRelationship
linkRelationship.description: Indicates the relationship type of a Web link.

httpMethod.name: httpMethod
httpMethod.description: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

numberOfBathroomsTotal.name: numberOfBathroomsTotal
numberOfBathroomsTotal.description: The total integer number of bathrooms in some [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions as [documented in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsTotalInteger+Field): "The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example for a property with two Full Bathrooms and one Half Bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer will be 3.". See also [[numberOfRooms]].

browserRequirements.name: browserRequirements
browserRequirements.description: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

priceSpecification.name: priceSpecification
priceSpecification.description: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

numberOfAxles.name: numberOfAxles
numberOfAxles.description: The number of axles.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

exercisePlan.name: exercisePlan
exercisePlan.description: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

arrivalGate.name: arrivalGate
arrivalGate.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

speechToTextMarkup.name: speechToTextMarkup
speechToTextMarkup.description: Form of markup used. eg. [SSML](https://www.w3.org/TR/speech-synthesis11) or [IPA](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P898).

geoCrosses.name: geoCrosses
geoCrosses.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

earlyPrepaymentPenalty.name: earlyPrepaymentPenalty
earlyPrepaymentPenalty.description: The amount to be paid as a penalty in the event of early payment of the loan.

educationalLevel.name: educationalLevel
educationalLevel.description: The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

variesBy.name: variesBy
variesBy.description: Indicates the property or properties by which the variants in a [[ProductGroup]] vary, e.g. their size, color etc. Schema.org properties can be referenced by their short name e.g. "color"; terms defined elsewhere can be referenced with their URIs.

broadcastDisplayName.name: broadcastDisplayName
broadcastDisplayName.description: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

itemDefectReturnFees.name: itemDefectReturnFees
itemDefectReturnFees.description: The type of return fees for returns of defect products.

administrationRoute.name: administrationRoute
administrationRoute.description: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

eventSchedule.name: eventSchedule
eventSchedule.description: Associates an [[Event]] with a [[Schedule]]. There are circumstances where it is preferable to share a schedule for a series of repeating events rather than data on the individual events themselves. For example, a website or application might prefer to publish a schedule for a weekly gym class rather than provide data on every event. A schedule could be processed by applications to add forthcoming events to a calendar. An [[Event]] that is associated with a [[Schedule]] using this property should not have [[startDate]] or [[endDate]] properties. These are instead defined within the associated [[Schedule]], this avoids any ambiguity for clients using the data. The property might have repeated values to specify different schedules, e.g. for different months or seasons.

toLocation.name: toLocation
toLocation.description: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

applicantLocationRequirements.name: applicantLocationRequirements
applicantLocationRequirements.description: The location(s) applicants can apply from. This is usually used for telecommuting jobs where the applicant does not need to be in a physical office. Note: This should not be used for citizenship or work visa requirements.

postalCodePrefix.name: postalCodePrefix
postalCodePrefix.description: A defined range of postal codes indicated by a common textual prefix. Used for non-numeric systems such as UK.

sizeSystem.name: sizeSystem
sizeSystem.description: The size system used to identify a product's size. Typically either a standard (for example, "GS1" or "ISO-EN13402"), country code (for example "US" or "JP"), or a measuring system (for example "Metric" or "Imperial").

articleSection.name: articleSection
articleSection.description: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

subStageSuffix.name: subStageSuffix
subStageSuffix.description: The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

regionDrained.name: regionDrained
regionDrained.description: The anatomical or organ system drained by this vessel; generally refers to a specific part of an organ.

applicationContact.name: applicationContact
applicationContact.description: Contact details for further information relevant to this job posting.

numAdults.name: numAdults
numAdults.description: The number of adults staying in the unit.

customerRemorseReturnLabelSource.name: customerRemorseReturnLabelSource
customerRemorseReturnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned due to customer remorse.

activityDuration.name: activityDuration
activityDuration.description: Length of time to engage in the activity.

validFor.name: validFor
validFor.description: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

primaryImageOfPage.name: primaryImageOfPage
primaryImageOfPage.description: Indicates the main image on the page.

penciler.name: penciler
penciler.description: The individual who draws the primary narrative artwork.

errorCode.name: errorCode
errorCode.description: Application or platform dependant error code.

sender.name: sender
sender.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

bestRating.name: bestRating
bestRating.description: The highest value allowed in this rating system.

character.name: character
character.description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

copyrightHolder.name: copyrightHolder
copyrightHolder.description: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

runtimePlatform.name: runtimePlatform
runtimePlatform.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

target.name: target
target.description: Indicates a target EntryPoint, or url, for an Action.

securityClearanceRequirement.name: securityClearanceRequirement
securityClearanceRequirement.description: A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.

gameAvailabilityType.name: gameAvailabilityType
gameAvailabilityType.description: Indicates the availability type of the game content associated with this action, such as whether it is a full version or a demo.

specialCommitments.name: specialCommitments
specialCommitments.description: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

departureStation.name: departureStation
departureStation.description: The station from which the train departs.

issuedBy.name: issuedBy
issuedBy.description: The organization issuing the item, for example a [[Permit]], [[Ticket]], or [[Certification]].

backstory.name: backstory
backstory.description: For an [[Article]], typically a [[NewsArticle]], the backstory property provides a textual summary giving a brief explanation of why and how an article was created. In a journalistic setting this could include information about reporting process, methods, interviews, data sources, etc.

dateModified.name: dateModified
dateModified.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

departureTerminal.name: departureTerminal
departureTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

resultComment.name: resultComment
resultComment.description: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

mediaItemAppearance.name: mediaItemAppearance
mediaItemAppearance.description: In the context of a [[MediaReview]], indicates specific media item(s) that are grouped using a [[MediaReviewItem]].

currentExchangeRate.name: currentExchangeRate
currentExchangeRate.description: The current price of a currency.

availabilityEnds.name: availabilityEnds
availabilityEnds.description: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

priceValidUntil.name: priceValidUntil
priceValidUntil.description: The date after which the price is no longer available.

includedInHealthInsurancePlan.name: includedInHealthInsurancePlan
includedInHealthInsurancePlan.description: The insurance plans that cover this drug.

hasTierRequirement.name: hasTierRequirement
hasTierRequirement.description: A requirement for a user to join a membership tier, for example: a CreditCard if the tier requires sign up for a credit card, A UnitPriceSpecification if the user is required to pay a (periodic) fee, or a MonetaryAmount if the user needs to spend a minimum amount to join the tier. If a tier is free to join then this property does not need to be specified.

afterMedia.name: afterMedia
afterMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

availableAtOrFrom.name: availableAtOrFrom
availableAtOrFrom.description: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

cvdNumC19OverflowPats.name: cvdNumC19OverflowPats
cvdNumC19OverflowPats.description: numc19overflowpats - ED/OVERFLOW: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed.

sensoryUnit.name: sensoryUnit
sensoryUnit.description: The neurological pathway extension that inputs and sends information to the brain or spinal cord.

cvdNumTotBeds.name: cvdNumTotBeds
cvdNumTotBeds.description: numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed, ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.

healthcareReportingData.name: healthcareReportingData
healthcareReportingData.description: Indicates data describing a hospital, e.g. a CDC [[CDCPMDRecord]] or as some kind of [[Dataset]].

dissolutionDate.name: dissolutionDate
dissolutionDate.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

cutoffTime.name: cutoffTime
cutoffTime.description: Order cutoff time allows merchants to describe the time after which they will no longer process orders received on that day. For orders processed after cutoff time, one day gets added to the delivery time estimate. This property is expected to be most typically used via the [[ShippingRateSettings]] publication pattern. The time is indicated using the ISO-8601 Time format, e.g. "23:30:00-05:00" would represent 6:30 pm Eastern Standard Time (EST) which is 5 hours behind Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

cvdNumC19HospPats.name: cvdNumC19HospPats
cvdNumC19HospPats.description: numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

unnamedSourcesPolicy.name: unnamedSourcesPolicy
unnamedSourcesPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

targetName.name: targetName
targetName.description: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

estimatedSalary.name: estimatedSalary
estimatedSalary.description: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

drug.name: drug
drug.description: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

annualPercentageRate.name: annualPercentageRate
annualPercentageRate.description: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

owns.name: owns
owns.description: Things owned by the organization or person.

incentiveAmount.name: incentiveAmount
incentiveAmount.description: Describes the amount that can be redeemed from this incentive. [[QuantitativeValue]]: Use this for incentives based on price (either raw amount or percentage-based). For a raw amount example, "You can claim $2,500 - $7,500 from the total cost of installation" would be represented as the following: { "@type": "QuantitativeValue", minValue: 2500, maxValue: 7500, "unitCode": "USD" } [[QuantitivateValue]] can also be used for percentage amounts. In such cases, value is used to represent the incentives percentage, while maxValue represents a limit (if one exists) to that incentive. The unitCode should be 'P1' and the unitText should be '%', while valueReference should be used for holding the currency type. For example, "You can claim up to 30% of the total cost of installation, up to a maximum of $7,500" would be: { "@type": "QuantitativeValue", "value": 30, "unitCode": "P1", "unitText": "%", maxValue: 7500, valueReference: USD } [[UnitPriceSpecification]]: Use this for incentives that are based on amounts rather than price. For example, a net metering rebate that pays $10/kWh, up to $1,000: { "@type": "UnitPriceSpecification", "price": 10, "priceCurrency": "USD", "referenceQuantity": 1, "unitCode": "DO3", "unitText": "kw/h", "maxPrice": 1000, "description": "$10 / kwh up to $1000" } [[LoanOrCredit]]: Use for incentives that are loan based. For example, a loan of $4,000 - $50,000 with a repayment term of 10 years, interest free would look like: { "@type": "LoanOrCredit", "loanTerm": { "@type":"QuantitativeValue", "value":"10", "unitCode": "ANN" }, "amount":[ { "@type": "QuantitativeValue", "Name":"fixed interest rate", "value":"0", }, ], "amount":[ { "@type": "MonetaryAmount", "Name":"min loan amount", "value":"4000", "currency":"CAD" }, { "@type": "MonetaryAmount", "Name":"max loan amount", "value":"50000", "currency":"CAD" } ], } In summary: Use [[QuantitativeValue]] for absolute/percentage-based incentives applied on the price of a good/service. Use [[UnitPriceSpecification]] for incentives based on a per-unit basis (e.g. net metering). Use [[LoanOrCredit]] for loans/credits. .

The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
